{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01Su9VFKu4nn6bBjhyxcemFz","type":"tool_result","content":"     1ŌåÆ<workflow>\n     2ŌåÆ  <critical>The workflow execution engine is governed by: {project-root}/_bmad/core/tasks/workflow.xml</critical>\n     3ŌåÆ  <critical>You MUST have already loaded and processed: {installed_path}/workflow.yaml</critical>\n     4ŌåÆ  <critical>Communicate all responses in {communication_language} and generate all documents in {document_output_language}</critical>\n     5ŌåÆ\n     6ŌåÆ  <critical>­¤öź CRITICAL MISSION: You are creating the ULTIMATE story context engine that prevents LLM developer mistakes, omissions or\n     7ŌåÆ    disasters! ­¤öź</critical>\n     8ŌåÆ  <critical>Your purpose is NOT to copy from epics - it's to create a comprehensive, optimized story file that gives the DEV agent\n     9ŌåÆ    EVERYTHING needed for flawless implementation</critical>\n    10ŌåÆ  <critical>COMMON LLM MISTAKES TO PREVENT: reinventing wheels, wrong libraries, wrong file locations, breaking regressions, ignoring UX,\n    11ŌåÆ    vague implementations, lying about completion, not learning from past work</critical>\n    12ŌåÆ  <critical>­¤Ü© EXHAUSTIVE ANALYSIS REQUIRED: You must thoroughly analyze ALL artifacts to extract critical context - do NOT be lazy or skim!\n    13ŌåÆ    This is the most important function in the entire development process!</critical>\n    14ŌåÆ  <critical>­¤ö¼ UTILIZE SUBPROCESSES AND SUBAGENTS: Use research subagents, subprocesses or parallel processing if available to thoroughly\n    15ŌåÆ    analyze different artifacts simultaneously and thoroughly</critical>\n    16ŌåÆ  <critical>ŌØō SAVE QUESTIONS: If you think of questions or clarifications during analysis, save them for the end after the complete story is\n    17ŌåÆ    written</critical>\n    18ŌåÆ  <critical>­¤Ä» ZERO USER INTERVENTION: Process should be fully automated except for initial epic/story selection or missing documents</critical>\n    19ŌåÆ\n    20ŌåÆ  <step n=\"1\" goal=\"Determine target story\">\n    21ŌåÆ    <check if=\"{{story_path}} is provided by user or user provided the epic and story number such as 2-4 or 1.6 or epic 1 story 5\">\n    22ŌåÆ      <action>Parse user-provided story path: extract epic_num, story_num, story_title from format like \"1-2-user-auth\"</action>\n    23ŌåÆ      <action>Set {{epic_num}}, {{story_num}}, {{story_key}} from user input</action>\n    24ŌåÆ      <action>GOTO step 2a</action>\n    25ŌåÆ    </check>\n    26ŌåÆ\n    27ŌåÆ    <action>Check if {{sprint_status}} file exists for auto discover</action>\n    28ŌåÆ    <check if=\"sprint status file does NOT exist\">\n    29ŌåÆ      <output>­¤Ü½ No sprint status file found and no story specified</output>\n    30ŌåÆ      <output>\n    31ŌåÆ        **Required Options:**\n    32ŌåÆ        1. Run `sprint-planning` to initialize sprint tracking (recommended)\n    33ŌåÆ        2. Provide specific epic-story number to create (e.g., \"1-2-user-auth\")\n    34ŌåÆ        3. Provide path to story documents if sprint status doesn't exist yet\n    35ŌåÆ      </output>\n    36ŌåÆ      <ask>Choose option [1], provide epic-story number, path to story docs, or [q] to quit:</ask>\n    37ŌåÆ\n    38ŌåÆ      <check if=\"user chooses 'q'\">\n    39ŌåÆ        <action>HALT - No work needed</action>\n    40ŌåÆ      </check>\n    41ŌåÆ\n    42ŌåÆ      <check if=\"user chooses '1'\">\n    43ŌåÆ        <output>Run sprint-planning workflow first to create sprint-status.yaml</output>\n    44ŌåÆ        <action>HALT - User needs to run sprint-planning</action>\n    45ŌåÆ      </check>\n    46ŌåÆ\n    47ŌåÆ      <check if=\"user provides epic-story number\">\n    48ŌåÆ        <action>Parse user input: extract epic_num, story_num, story_title</action>\n    49ŌåÆ        <action>Set {{epic_num}}, {{story_num}}, {{story_key}} from user input</action>\n    50ŌåÆ        <action>GOTO step 2a</action>\n    51ŌåÆ      </check>\n    52ŌåÆ\n    53ŌåÆ      <check if=\"user provides story docs path\">\n    54ŌåÆ        <action>Use user-provided path for story documents</action>\n    55ŌåÆ        <action>GOTO step 2a</action>\n    56ŌåÆ      </check>\n    57ŌåÆ    </check>\n    58ŌåÆ\n    59ŌåÆ    <!-- Auto-discover from sprint status only if no user input -->\n    60ŌåÆ    <check if=\"no user input provided\">\n    61ŌåÆ      <critical>MUST read COMPLETE {sprint_status} file from start to end to preserve order</critical>\n    62ŌåÆ      <action>Load the FULL file: {{sprint_status}}</action>\n    63ŌåÆ      <action>Read ALL lines from beginning to end - do not skip any content</action>\n    64ŌåÆ      <action>Parse the development_status section completely</action>\n    65ŌåÆ\n    66ŌåÆ      <action>Find the FIRST story (by reading in order from top to bottom) where:\n    67ŌåÆ        - Key matches pattern: number-number-name (e.g., \"1-2-user-auth\")\n    68ŌåÆ        - NOT an epic key (epic-X) or retrospective (epic-X-retrospective)\n    69ŌåÆ        - Status value equals \"backlog\"\n    70ŌåÆ      </action>\n    71ŌåÆ\n    72ŌåÆ      <check if=\"no backlog story found\">\n    73ŌåÆ        <output>­¤ōŗ No backlog stories found in sprint-status.yaml\n    74ŌåÆ\n    75ŌåÆ          All stories are either already created, in progress, or done.\n    76ŌåÆ\n    77ŌåÆ          **Options:**\n    78ŌåÆ          1. Run sprint-planning to refresh story tracking\n    79ŌåÆ          2. Load PM agent and run correct-course to add more stories\n    80ŌåÆ          3. Check if current sprint is complete and run retrospective\n    81ŌåÆ        </output>\n    82ŌåÆ        <action>HALT</action>\n    83ŌåÆ      </check>\n    84ŌåÆ\n    85ŌåÆ      <action>Extract from found story key (e.g., \"1-2-user-authentication\"):\n    86ŌåÆ        - epic_num: first number before dash (e.g., \"1\")\n    87ŌåÆ        - story_num: second number after first dash (e.g., \"2\")\n    88ŌåÆ        - story_title: remainder after second dash (e.g., \"user-authentication\")\n    89ŌåÆ      </action>\n    90ŌåÆ      <action>Set {{story_id}} = \"{{epic_num}}.{{story_num}}\"</action>\n    91ŌåÆ      <action>Store story_key for later use (e.g., \"1-2-user-authentication\")</action>\n    92ŌåÆ\n    93ŌåÆ      <!-- Mark epic as in-progress if this is first story -->\n    94ŌåÆ      <action>Check if this is the first story in epic {{epic_num}} by looking for {{epic_num}}-1-* pattern</action>\n    95ŌåÆ      <check if=\"this is first story in epic {{epic_num}}\">\n    96ŌåÆ        <action>Load {{sprint_status}} and check epic-{{epic_num}} status</action>\n    97ŌåÆ        <action>If epic status is \"backlog\" ŌåÆ update to \"in-progress\"</action>\n    98ŌåÆ        <action>If epic status is \"contexted\" (legacy status) ŌåÆ update to \"in-progress\" (backward compatibility)</action>\n    99ŌåÆ        <action>If epic status is \"in-progress\" ŌåÆ no change needed</action>\n   100ŌåÆ        <check if=\"epic status is 'done'\">\n   101ŌåÆ          <output>­¤Ü½ ERROR: Cannot create story in completed epic</output>\n   102ŌåÆ          <output>Epic {{epic_num}} is marked as 'done'. All stories are complete.</output>\n   103ŌåÆ          <output>If you need to add more work, either:</output>\n   104ŌåÆ          <output>1. Manually change epic status back to 'in-progress' in sprint-status.yaml</output>\n   105ŌåÆ          <output>2. Create a new epic for additional work</output>\n   106ŌåÆ          <action>HALT - Cannot proceed</action>\n   107ŌåÆ        </check>\n   108ŌåÆ        <check if=\"epic status is not one of: backlog, contexted, in-progress, done\">\n   109ŌåÆ          <output>­¤Ü½ ERROR: Invalid epic status '{{epic_status}}'</output>\n   110ŌåÆ          <output>Epic {{epic_num}} has invalid status. Expected: backlog, in-progress, or done</output>\n   111ŌåÆ          <output>Please fix sprint-status.yaml manually or run sprint-planning to regenerate</output>\n   112ŌåÆ          <action>HALT - Cannot proceed</action>\n   113ŌåÆ        </check>\n   114ŌåÆ        <output>­¤ōŖ Epic {{epic_num}} status updated to in-progress</output>\n   115ŌåÆ      </check>\n   116ŌåÆ\n   117ŌåÆ      <action>GOTO step 2a</action>\n   118ŌåÆ    </check>\n   119ŌåÆ    <action>Load the FULL file: {{sprint_status}}</action>\n   120ŌåÆ    <action>Read ALL lines from beginning to end - do not skip any content</action>\n   121ŌåÆ    <action>Parse the development_status section completely</action>\n   122ŌåÆ\n   123ŌåÆ    <action>Find the FIRST story (by reading in order from top to bottom) where:\n   124ŌåÆ      - Key matches pattern: number-number-name (e.g., \"1-2-user-auth\")\n   125ŌåÆ      - NOT an epic key (epic-X) or retrospective (epic-X-retrospective)\n   126ŌåÆ      - Status value equals \"backlog\"\n   127ŌåÆ    </action>\n   128ŌåÆ\n   129ŌåÆ    <check if=\"no backlog story found\">\n   130ŌåÆ      <output>­¤ōŗ No backlog stories found in sprint-status.yaml\n   131ŌåÆ\n   132ŌåÆ        All stories are either already created, in progress, or done.\n   133ŌåÆ\n   134ŌåÆ        **Options:**\n   135ŌåÆ        1. Run sprint-planning to refresh story tracking\n   136ŌåÆ        2. Load PM agent and run correct-course to add more stories\n   137ŌåÆ        3. Check if current sprint is complete and run retrospective\n   138ŌåÆ      </output>\n   139ŌåÆ      <action>HALT</action>\n   140ŌåÆ    </check>\n   141ŌåÆ\n   142ŌåÆ    <action>Extract from found story key (e.g., \"1-2-user-authentication\"):\n   143ŌåÆ      - epic_num: first number before dash (e.g., \"1\")\n   144ŌåÆ      - story_num: second number after first dash (e.g., \"2\")\n   145ŌåÆ      - story_title: remainder after second dash (e.g., \"user-authentication\")\n   146ŌåÆ    </action>\n   147ŌåÆ    <action>Set {{story_id}} = \"{{epic_num}}.{{story_num}}\"</action>\n   148ŌåÆ    <action>Store story_key for later use (e.g., \"1-2-user-authentication\")</action>\n   149ŌåÆ\n   150ŌåÆ    <!-- Mark epic as in-progress if this is first story -->\n   151ŌåÆ    <action>Check if this is the first story in epic {{epic_num}} by looking for {{epic_num}}-1-* pattern</action>\n   152ŌåÆ    <check if=\"this is first story in epic {{epic_num}}\">\n   153ŌåÆ      <action>Load {{sprint_status}} and check epic-{{epic_num}} status</action>\n   154ŌåÆ      <action>If epic status is \"backlog\" ŌåÆ update to \"in-progress\"</action>\n   155ŌåÆ      <action>If epic status is \"contexted\" (legacy status) ŌåÆ update to \"in-progress\" (backward compatibility)</action>\n   156ŌåÆ      <action>If epic status is \"in-progress\" ŌåÆ no change needed</action>\n   157ŌåÆ      <check if=\"epic status is 'done'\">\n   158ŌåÆ        <output>­¤Ü½ ERROR: Cannot create story in completed epic</output>\n   159ŌåÆ        <output>Epic {{epic_num}} is marked as 'done'. All stories are complete.</output>\n   160ŌåÆ        <output>If you need to add more work, either:</output>\n   161ŌåÆ        <output>1. Manually change epic status back to 'in-progress' in sprint-status.yaml</output>\n   162ŌåÆ        <output>2. Create a new epic for additional work</output>\n   163ŌåÆ        <action>HALT - Cannot proceed</action>\n   164ŌåÆ      </check>\n   165ŌåÆ      <check if=\"epic status is not one of: backlog, contexted, in-progress, done\">\n   166ŌåÆ        <output>­¤Ü½ ERROR: Invalid epic status '{{epic_status}}'</output>\n   167ŌåÆ        <output>Epic {{epic_num}} has invalid status. Expected: backlog, in-progress, or done</output>\n   168ŌåÆ        <output>Please fix sprint-status.yaml manually or run sprint-planning to regenerate</output>\n   169ŌåÆ        <action>HALT - Cannot proceed</action>\n   170ŌåÆ      </check>\n   171ŌåÆ      <output>­¤ōŖ Epic {{epic_num}} status updated to in-progress</output>\n   172ŌåÆ    </check>\n   173ŌåÆ\n   174ŌåÆ    <action>GOTO step 2a</action>\n   175ŌåÆ  </step>\n   176ŌåÆ\n   177ŌåÆ  <step n=\"2\" goal=\"Load and analyze core artifacts\">\n   178ŌåÆ    <critical>­¤ö¼ EXHAUSTIVE ARTIFACT ANALYSIS - This is where you prevent future developer fuckups!</critical>\n   179ŌåÆ\n   180ŌåÆ    <!-- Load all available content through discovery protocol -->\n   181ŌåÆ    <invoke-protocol\n   182ŌåÆ      name=\"discover_inputs\" />\n   183ŌåÆ    <note>Available content: {epics_content}, {prd_content}, {architecture_content}, {ux_content},\n   184ŌåÆ    {project_context}</note>\n   185ŌåÆ\n   186ŌåÆ    <!-- Analyze epics file for story foundation -->\n   187ŌåÆ    <action>From {epics_content}, extract Epic {{epic_num}} complete context:</action> **EPIC ANALYSIS:** - Epic\n   188ŌåÆ    objectives and business value - ALL stories in this epic for cross-story context - Our specific story's requirements, user story\n   189ŌåÆ    statement, acceptance criteria - Technical requirements and constraints - Dependencies on other stories/epics - Source hints pointing to\n   190ŌåÆ    original documents <!-- Extract specific story requirements -->\n   191ŌåÆ    <action>Extract our story ({{epic_num}}-{{story_num}}) details:</action> **STORY FOUNDATION:** - User story statement\n   192ŌåÆ    (As a, I want, so that) - Detailed acceptance criteria (already BDD formatted) - Technical requirements specific to this story -\n   193ŌåÆ    Business context and value - Success criteria\n   194ŌåÆ\n   195ŌåÆ    <!-- SPEC COVERAGE PASS: ACs from epics are a starting point, not the final set -->\n   196ŌåÆ    <critical>­¤Ä» SPEC COVERAGE ŌĆö ACs must cover UX/PRD behavioral requirements, not just epic bullet points!</critical>\n   197ŌåÆ    <action>Cross-reference epic ACs against {ux_content} and {prd_content} for this story's scope:\n   198ŌåÆ      - For each UX/PRD behavioral requirement within this story's scope, check if an existing AC covers it\n   199ŌåÆ      - If a requirement has no matching AC, draft a new AC that describes the observable user-facing behavior\n   200ŌåÆ      - ACs must describe WHAT THE USER SEES OR EXPERIENCES, not implementation artifacts\n   201ŌåÆ        BAD:  \"Given startRenderer() is called, Then it returns a RendererHandle with update() method\"\n   202ŌåÆ        GOOD: \"Given Claude is executing tools, When the operator watches the terminal, Then they see each active tool with a spinner and completed tools as permanent lines\"\n   203ŌåÆ      - Each AC should be verifiable by observing the running system, not just by reading code\n   204ŌåÆ      - Balance: cover all spec requirements but don't over-specify implementation details\n   205ŌåÆ    </action>\n   206ŌåÆ    <action>Store the merged AC list (epic ACs + spec-derived ACs) as the final acceptance criteria for the story</action>\n   207ŌåÆ\n   208ŌåÆ    <!-- Previous story analysis for context continuity -->\n   209ŌåÆ    <check if=\"story_num > 1\">\n   210ŌåÆ      <action>Find {{previous_story_num}}: scan {implementation_artifacts} for the story file in epic {{epic_num}} with the highest story number less than {{story_num}}</action>\n   211ŌåÆ      <action>Load previous story file: {implementation_artifacts}/{{epic_num}}-{{previous_story_num}}-*.md</action> **PREVIOUS STORY INTELLIGENCE:** -\n   212ŌåÆ    Dev notes and learnings from previous story - Review feedback and corrections needed - Files that were created/modified and their\n   213ŌåÆ    patterns - Testing approaches that worked/didn't work - Problems encountered and solutions found - Code patterns established <action>Extract\n   214ŌåÆ    all learnings that could impact current story implementation</action>\n   215ŌåÆ    </check>\n   216ŌåÆ\n   217ŌåÆ    <!-- Git intelligence for previous work patterns -->\n   218ŌåÆ    <check\n   219ŌåÆ      if=\"previous story exists AND git repository detected\">\n   220ŌåÆ      <action>Get last 5 commit titles to understand recent work patterns</action>\n   221ŌåÆ      <action>Analyze 1-5 most recent commits for relevance to current story:\n   222ŌåÆ        - Files created/modified\n   223ŌåÆ        - Code patterns and conventions used\n   224ŌåÆ        - Library dependencies added/changed\n   225ŌåÆ        - Architecture decisions implemented\n   226ŌåÆ        - Testing approaches used\n   227ŌåÆ      </action>\n   228ŌåÆ      <action>Extract actionable insights for current story implementation</action>\n   229ŌåÆ    </check>\n   230ŌåÆ  </step>\n   231ŌåÆ\n   232ŌåÆ  <step n=\"3\" goal=\"Architecture analysis for developer guardrails\">\n   233ŌåÆ    <critical>­¤ÅŚ’ĖÅ ARCHITECTURE INTELLIGENCE - Extract everything the developer MUST follow!</critical> **ARCHITECTURE DOCUMENT ANALYSIS:** <action>Systematically\n   234ŌåÆ    analyze architecture content for story-relevant requirements:</action>\n   235ŌåÆ\n   236ŌåÆ    <!-- Load architecture - single file or sharded -->\n   237ŌåÆ    <check if=\"architecture file is single file\">\n   238ŌåÆ      <action>Load complete {architecture_content}</action>\n   239ŌåÆ    </check>\n   240ŌåÆ    <check if=\"architecture is sharded to folder\">\n   241ŌåÆ      <action>Load architecture index and scan all architecture files</action>\n   242ŌåÆ    </check> **CRITICAL ARCHITECTURE EXTRACTION:** <action>For\n   243ŌåÆ    each architecture section, determine if relevant to this story:</action> - **Technical Stack:** Languages, frameworks, libraries with\n   244ŌåÆ    versions - **Code Structure:** Folder organization, naming conventions, file patterns - **API Patterns:** Service structure, endpoint\n   245ŌåÆ    patterns, data contracts - **Database Schemas:** Tables, relationships, constraints relevant to story - **Security Requirements:**\n   246ŌåÆ    Authentication patterns, authorization rules - **Performance Requirements:** Caching strategies, optimization patterns - **Testing\n   247ŌåÆ    Standards:** Testing frameworks, coverage expectations, test patterns - **Deployment Patterns:** Environment configurations, build\n   248ŌåÆ    processes - **Integration Patterns:** External service integrations, data flows <action>Extract any story-specific requirements that the\n   249ŌåÆ    developer MUST follow</action>\n   250ŌåÆ    <action>Identify any architectural decisions that override previous patterns</action>\n   251ŌåÆ  </step>\n   252ŌåÆ\n   253ŌåÆ  <step n=\"4\" goal=\"Web research for latest technical specifics\">\n   254ŌåÆ    <critical>­¤īÉ ENSURE LATEST TECH KNOWLEDGE - Prevent outdated implementations!</critical> **WEB INTELLIGENCE:** <action>Identify specific\n   255ŌåÆ    technical areas that require latest version knowledge:</action>\n   256ŌåÆ\n   257ŌåÆ    <!-- Check for libraries/frameworks mentioned in architecture -->\n   258ŌåÆ    <action>From architecture analysis, identify specific libraries, APIs, or\n   259ŌåÆ    frameworks</action>\n   260ŌåÆ    <action>For each critical technology, research latest stable version and key changes:\n   261ŌåÆ      - Latest API documentation and breaking changes\n   262ŌåÆ      - Security vulnerabilities or updates\n   263ŌåÆ      - Performance improvements or deprecations\n   264ŌåÆ      - Best practices for current version\n   265ŌåÆ    </action>\n   266ŌåÆ    **EXTERNAL CONTEXT INCLUSION:** <action>Include in story any critical latest information the developer needs:\n   267ŌåÆ      - Specific library versions and why chosen\n   268ŌåÆ      - API endpoints with parameters and authentication\n   269ŌåÆ      - Recent security patches or considerations\n   270ŌåÆ      - Performance optimization techniques\n   271ŌåÆ      - Migration considerations if upgrading\n   272ŌåÆ    </action>\n   273ŌåÆ  </step>\n   274ŌåÆ\n   275ŌåÆ  <step n=\"5\" goal=\"Create comprehensive story file\">\n   276ŌåÆ    <critical>­¤ōØ CREATE ULTIMATE STORY FILE - The developer's master implementation guide!</critical>\n   277ŌåÆ\n   278ŌåÆ    <action>Initialize from template.md:\n   279ŌåÆ    {default_output_file}</action>\n   280ŌåÆ    <template-output file=\"{default_output_file}\">story_header</template-output>\n   281ŌåÆ\n   282ŌåÆ    <!-- Story foundation from epics analysis -->\n   283ŌåÆ    <template-output\n   284ŌåÆ      file=\"{default_output_file}\">story_requirements</template-output>\n   285ŌåÆ\n   286ŌåÆ    <!-- FINAL AC QUALITY CHECK before writing the rest of the story -->\n   287ŌåÆ    <critical>­¤öŹ AC QUALITY GATE ŌĆö Review ACs before finalizing the story file</critical>\n   288ŌåÆ    <action>Before proceeding, review every AC in the story file:\n   289ŌåÆ      1. Does each AC describe observable user-facing behavior (not just code artifacts)?\n   290ŌåÆ         - REJECT: \"function X exists\", \"module exports Y\", \"returns RendererHandle\"\n   291ŌåÆ         - ACCEPT: \"operator sees X in the terminal\", \"command outputs Y\", \"dashboard displays Z\"\n   292ŌåÆ      2. Is every behavioral requirement from the UX spec and PRD (within this story's scope) covered by at least one AC?\n   293ŌåÆ         - If not, add the missing AC now\n   294ŌåÆ      3. Are ACs balanced ŌĆö specific enough to verify but not so narrow they miss the spirit of the requirement?\n   295ŌåÆ         - A single AC like \"header shows story key\" is too narrow if the spec says \"header shows story key, phase, elapsed time, and progress\"\n   296ŌåÆ         - Combine related display elements into one AC that covers the full expected output\n   297ŌåÆ      4. Can each AC be verified by running the system and observing output (not just reading source code)?\n   298ŌåÆ    </action>\n   299ŌåÆ\n   300ŌåÆ    <!-- Developer context section - MOST IMPORTANT PART -->\n   301ŌåÆ    <template-output file=\"{default_output_file}\">\n   302ŌåÆ    developer_context_section</template-output> **DEV AGENT GUARDRAILS:** <template-output file=\"{default_output_file}\">\n   303ŌåÆ    technical_requirements</template-output>\n   304ŌåÆ    <template-output file=\"{default_output_file}\">architecture_compliance</template-output>\n   305ŌåÆ    <template-output\n   306ŌåÆ      file=\"{default_output_file}\">library_framework_requirements</template-output>\n   307ŌåÆ    <template-output file=\"{default_output_file}\">\n   308ŌåÆ    file_structure_requirements</template-output>\n   309ŌåÆ    <template-output file=\"{default_output_file}\">testing_requirements</template-output>\n   310ŌåÆ\n   311ŌåÆ    <!-- Previous story intelligence -->\n   312ŌåÆ    <check\n   313ŌåÆ      if=\"previous story learnings available\">\n   314ŌåÆ      <template-output file=\"{default_output_file}\">previous_story_intelligence</template-output>\n   315ŌåÆ    </check>\n   316ŌåÆ\n   317ŌåÆ    <!-- Git intelligence -->\n   318ŌåÆ    <check\n   319ŌåÆ      if=\"git analysis completed\">\n   320ŌåÆ      <template-output file=\"{default_output_file}\">git_intelligence_summary</template-output>\n   321ŌåÆ    </check>\n   322ŌåÆ\n   323ŌåÆ    <!-- Latest technical specifics -->\n   324ŌåÆ    <check if=\"web research completed\">\n   325ŌåÆ      <template-output file=\"{default_output_file}\">latest_tech_information</template-output>\n   326ŌåÆ    </check>\n   327ŌåÆ\n   328ŌåÆ    <!-- Project context reference -->\n   329ŌåÆ    <template-output\n   330ŌåÆ      file=\"{default_output_file}\">project_context_reference</template-output>\n   331ŌåÆ\n   332ŌåÆ    <!-- Final status update -->\n   333ŌåÆ    <template-output file=\"{default_output_file}\">\n   334ŌåÆ    story_completion_status</template-output>\n   335ŌåÆ\n   336ŌåÆ    <!-- CRITICAL: Set status to ready-for-dev -->\n   337ŌåÆ    <action>Set story Status to: \"ready-for-dev\"</action>\n   338ŌåÆ    <action>Add completion note: \"Ultimate\n   339ŌåÆ    context engine analysis completed - comprehensive developer guide created\"</action>\n   340ŌåÆ  </step>\n   341ŌåÆ\n   342ŌåÆ  <step n=\"6\" goal=\"Update sprint status and finalize\">\n   343ŌåÆ    <invoke-task>Validate against checklist at {installed_path}/checklist.md using _bmad/core/tasks/validate-workflow.xml</invoke-task>\n   344ŌåÆ    <action>Save story document unconditionally</action>\n   345ŌåÆ\n   346ŌåÆ    <!-- Update sprint status -->\n   347ŌåÆ    <check if=\"sprint status file exists\">\n   348ŌåÆ      <action>Update {{sprint_status}}</action>\n   349ŌåÆ      <action>Load the FULL file and read all development_status entries</action>\n   350ŌåÆ      <action>Find development_status key matching {{story_key}}</action>\n   351ŌåÆ      <action>Verify current status is \"backlog\" (expected previous state)</action>\n   352ŌåÆ      <action>Update development_status[{{story_key}}] = \"ready-for-dev\"</action>\n   353ŌåÆ      <action>Save file, preserving ALL comments and structure including STATUS DEFINITIONS</action>\n   354ŌåÆ    </check>\n   355ŌåÆ\n   356ŌåÆ    <action>Report completion</action>\n   357ŌåÆ    <output>**­¤Ä» ULTIMATE BMad Method STORY CONTEXT CREATED, {user_name}!**\n   358ŌåÆ\n   359ŌåÆ      **Story Details:**\n   360ŌåÆ      - Story ID: {{story_id}}\n   361ŌåÆ      - Story Key: {{story_key}}\n   362ŌåÆ      - File: {{story_file}}\n   363ŌåÆ      - Status: ready-for-dev\n   364ŌåÆ\n   365ŌåÆ      **Next Steps:**\n   366ŌåÆ      1. Review the comprehensive story in {{story_file}}\n   367ŌåÆ      2. Run dev agents `dev-story` for optimized implementation\n   368ŌåÆ      3. Run `code-review` when complete (auto-marks done)\n   369ŌåÆ      4. Optional: If Test Architect module installed, run `/bmad:tea:automate` after `dev-story` to generate guardrail tests\n   370ŌåÆ\n   371ŌåÆ      **The developer now has everything needed for flawless implementation!**\n   372ŌåÆ    </output>\n   373ŌåÆ  </step>\n   374ŌåÆ\n   375ŌåÆ</workflow>\n   376ŌåÆ"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01SqkcCz91dsjFJacd7fAMKf","session_id":"010b7052-acb2-4a98-9861-0b5f61bbdbf0","uuid":"19b3edda-3e57-4205-97ea-ae3408ed3bcd","timestamp":"2026-03-24T11:58:49.757Z"}
