{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01J2NKP3QpW9vawbgUZr44Ck","type":"tool_result","content":"     1ŌåÆ# ­¤Ä» Story Context Quality Competition Prompt\n     2ŌåÆ\n     3ŌåÆ## **­¤öź CRITICAL MISSION: Outperform and Fix the Original Create-Story LLM**\n     4ŌåÆ\n     5ŌåÆYou are an independent quality validator in a **FRESH CONTEXT**. Your mission is to **thoroughly review** a story file that was generated by the create-story workflow and **systematically identify any mistakes, omissions, or disasters** that the original LLM missed.\n     6ŌåÆ\n     7ŌåÆ**Your purpose is NOT just to validate - it's to FIX and PREVENT LLM developer mistakes, omissions, or disasters!**\n     8ŌåÆ\n     9ŌåÆ### **­¤Ü© CRITICAL MISTAKES TO PREVENT:**\n    10ŌåÆ\n    11ŌåÆ- **Reinventing wheels** - Creating duplicate functionality instead of reusing existing\n    12ŌåÆ- **Wrong libraries** - Using incorrect frameworks, versions, or dependencies\n    13ŌåÆ- **Wrong file locations** - Violating project structure and organization\n    14ŌåÆ- **Breaking regressions** - Implementing changes that break existing functionality\n    15ŌåÆ- **Ignoring UX** - Not following user experience design requirements\n    16ŌåÆ- **Vague implementations** - Creating unclear, ambiguous implementations\n    17ŌåÆ- **Lying about completion** - Implementing incorrectly or incompletely\n    18ŌåÆ- **Not learning from past work** - Ignoring previous story learnings and patterns\n    19ŌåÆ\n    20ŌåÆ### **­¤Ü© EXHAUSTIVE ANALYSIS REQUIRED:**\n    21ŌåÆ\n    22ŌåÆYou must thoroughly analyze **ALL artifacts** to extract critical context - do NOT be lazy or skim! This is the most important quality control function in the entire development process!\n    23ŌåÆ\n    24ŌåÆ### **­¤ö¼ UTILIZE SUBPROCESSES AND SUBAGENTS:**\n    25ŌåÆ\n    26ŌåÆUse research subagents, subprocesses, or parallel processing if available to thoroughly analyze different artifacts **simultaneously and thoroughly**. Leave no stone unturned!\n    27ŌåÆ\n    28ŌåÆ### **­¤Ä» COMPETITIVE EXCELLENCE:**\n    29ŌåÆ\n    30ŌåÆThis is a COMPETITION to create the **ULTIMATE story context** that makes LLM developer mistakes **IMPOSSIBLE**!\n    31ŌåÆ\n    32ŌåÆ## **­¤ÜĆ HOW TO USE THIS CHECKLIST**\n    33ŌåÆ\n    34ŌåÆ### **When Running from Create-Story Workflow:**\n    35ŌåÆ\n    36ŌåÆ- The `{project-root}/_bmad/core/tasks/validate-workflow.xml` framework will automatically:\n    37ŌåÆ  - Load this checklist file\n    38ŌåÆ  - Load the newly created story file (`{story_file_path}`)\n    39ŌåÆ  - Load workflow variables from `{installed_path}/workflow.yaml`\n    40ŌåÆ  - Execute the validation process\n    41ŌåÆ\n    42ŌåÆ### **When Running in Fresh Context:**\n    43ŌåÆ\n    44ŌåÆ- User should provide the story file path being reviewed\n    45ŌåÆ- Load the story file directly\n    46ŌåÆ- Load the corresponding workflow.yaml for variable context\n    47ŌåÆ- Proceed with systematic analysis\n    48ŌåÆ\n    49ŌåÆ### **Required Inputs:**\n    50ŌåÆ\n    51ŌåÆ- **Story file**: The story file to review and improve\n    52ŌåÆ- **Workflow variables**: From workflow.yaml (implementation_artifacts, epics_file, etc.)\n    53ŌåÆ- **Source documents**: Epics, architecture, etc. (discovered or provided)\n    54ŌåÆ- **Validation framework**: `validate-workflow.xml` (handles checklist execution)\n    55ŌåÆ\n    56ŌåÆ---\n    57ŌåÆ\n    58ŌåÆ## **­¤ö¼ SYSTEMATIC RE-ANALYSIS APPROACH**\n    59ŌåÆ\n    60ŌåÆYou will systematically re-do the entire story creation process, but with a critical eye for what the original LLM might have missed:\n    61ŌåÆ\n    62ŌåÆ### **Step 1: Load and Understand the Target**\n    63ŌåÆ\n    64ŌåÆ1. **Load the workflow configuration**: `{installed_path}/workflow.yaml` for variable inclusion\n    65ŌåÆ2. **Load the story file**: `{story_file_path}` (provided by user or discovered)\n    66ŌåÆ3. **Load validation framework**: `{project-root}/_bmad/core/tasks/validate-workflow.xml`\n    67ŌåÆ4. **Extract metadata**: epic_num, story_num, story_key, story_title from story file\n    68ŌåÆ5. **Resolve all workflow variables**: implementation_artifacts, epics_file, architecture_file, etc.\n    69ŌåÆ6. **Understand current status**: What story implementation guidance is currently provided?\n    70ŌåÆ\n    71ŌåÆ**Note:** If running in fresh context, user should provide the story file path being reviewed. If running from create-story workflow, the validation framework will automatically discover the checklist and story file.\n    72ŌåÆ\n    73ŌåÆ### **Step 2: Exhaustive Source Document Analysis**\n    74ŌåÆ\n    75ŌåÆ**­¤öź CRITICAL: Treat this like YOU are creating the story from scratch to PREVENT DISASTERS!**\n    76ŌåÆ**Discover everything the original LLM missed that could cause developer mistakes, omissions, or disasters!**\n    77ŌåÆ\n    78ŌåÆ#### **2.1 Epics and Stories Analysis**\n    79ŌåÆ\n    80ŌåÆ- Load `{epics_file}` (or sharded equivalents)\n    81ŌåÆ- Extract **COMPLETE Epic {{epic_num}} context**:\n    82ŌåÆ  - Epic objectives and business value\n    83ŌåÆ  - ALL stories in this epic (for cross-story context)\n    84ŌåÆ  - Our specific story's requirements, acceptance criteria\n    85ŌåÆ  - Technical requirements and constraints\n    86ŌåÆ  - Cross-story dependencies and prerequisites\n    87ŌåÆ\n    88ŌåÆ#### **2.2 Architecture Deep-Dive**\n    89ŌåÆ\n    90ŌåÆ- Load `{architecture_file}` (single or sharded)\n    91ŌåÆ- **Systematically scan for ANYTHING relevant to this story:**\n    92ŌåÆ  - Technical stack with versions (languages, frameworks, libraries)\n    93ŌåÆ  - Code structure and organization patterns\n    94ŌåÆ  - API design patterns and contracts\n    95ŌåÆ  - Database schemas and relationships\n    96ŌåÆ  - Security requirements and patterns\n    97ŌåÆ  - Performance requirements and optimization strategies\n    98ŌåÆ  - Testing standards and frameworks\n    99ŌåÆ  - Deployment and environment patterns\n   100ŌåÆ  - Integration patterns and external services\n   101ŌåÆ\n   102ŌåÆ#### **2.3 Previous Story Intelligence (if applicable)**\n   103ŌåÆ\n   104ŌåÆ- If `story_num > 1`, load the previous story file\n   105ŌåÆ- Extract **actionable intelligence**:\n   106ŌåÆ  - Dev notes and learnings\n   107ŌåÆ  - Review feedback and corrections needed\n   108ŌåÆ  - Files created/modified and their patterns\n   109ŌåÆ  - Testing approaches that worked/didn't work\n   110ŌåÆ  - Problems encountered and solutions found\n   111ŌåÆ  - Code patterns and conventions established\n   112ŌåÆ\n   113ŌåÆ#### **2.4 Git History Analysis (if available)**\n   114ŌåÆ\n   115ŌåÆ- Analyze recent commits for patterns:\n   116ŌåÆ  - Files created/modified in previous work\n   117ŌåÆ  - Code patterns and conventions used\n   118ŌåÆ  - Library dependencies added/changed\n   119ŌåÆ  - Architecture decisions implemented\n   120ŌåÆ  - Testing approaches used\n   121ŌåÆ\n   122ŌåÆ#### **2.5 Latest Technical Research**\n   123ŌåÆ\n   124ŌåÆ- Identify any libraries/frameworks mentioned\n   125ŌåÆ- Research latest versions and critical information:\n   126ŌåÆ  - Breaking changes or security updates\n   127ŌåÆ  - Performance improvements or deprecations\n   128ŌåÆ  - Best practices for current versions\n   129ŌåÆ\n   130ŌåÆ### **Step 3: Disaster Prevention Gap Analysis**\n   131ŌåÆ\n   132ŌåÆ**­¤Ü© CRITICAL: Identify every mistake the original LLM missed that could cause DISASTERS!**\n   133ŌåÆ\n   134ŌåÆ#### **3.1 Reinvention Prevention Gaps**\n   135ŌåÆ\n   136ŌåÆ- **Wheel reinvention:** Areas where developer might create duplicate functionality\n   137ŌåÆ- **Code reuse opportunities** not identified that could prevent redundant work\n   138ŌåÆ- **Existing solutions** not mentioned that developer should extend instead of replace\n   139ŌåÆ\n   140ŌåÆ#### **3.2 Technical Specification DISASTERS**\n   141ŌåÆ\n   142ŌåÆ- **Wrong libraries/frameworks:** Missing version requirements that could cause compatibility issues\n   143ŌåÆ- **API contract violations:** Missing endpoint specifications that could break integrations\n   144ŌåÆ- **Database schema conflicts:** Missing requirements that could corrupt data\n   145ŌåÆ- **Security vulnerabilities:** Missing security requirements that could expose the system\n   146ŌåÆ- **Performance disasters:** Missing requirements that could cause system failures\n   147ŌåÆ\n   148ŌåÆ#### **3.3 File Structure DISASTERS**\n   149ŌåÆ\n   150ŌåÆ- **Wrong file locations:** Missing organization requirements that could break build processes\n   151ŌåÆ- **Coding standard violations:** Missing conventions that could create inconsistent codebase\n   152ŌåÆ- **Integration pattern breaks:** Missing data flow requirements that could cause system failures\n   153ŌåÆ- **Deployment failures:** Missing environment requirements that could prevent deployment\n   154ŌåÆ\n   155ŌåÆ#### **3.4 Regression DISASTERS**\n   156ŌåÆ\n   157ŌåÆ- **Breaking changes:** Missing requirements that could break existing functionality\n   158ŌåÆ- **Test failures:** Missing test requirements that could allow bugs to reach production\n   159ŌåÆ- **UX violations:** Missing user experience requirements that could ruin the product\n   160ŌåÆ- **Learning failures:** Missing previous story context that could repeat same mistakes\n   161ŌåÆ\n   162ŌåÆ#### **3.5 Implementation DISASTERS**\n   163ŌåÆ\n   164ŌåÆ- **Vague implementations:** Missing details that could lead to incorrect or incomplete work\n   165ŌåÆ- **Completion lies:** Missing acceptance criteria that could allow fake implementations\n   166ŌåÆ- **Scope creep:** Missing boundaries that could cause unnecessary work\n   167ŌåÆ- **Quality failures:** Missing quality requirements that could deliver broken features\n   168ŌåÆ\n   169ŌåÆ#### **3.6 Spec Coverage DISASTERS**\n   170ŌåÆ\n   171ŌåÆ- **Dropped requirements:** UX spec or PRD describes behavior within this story's scope that no AC covers. Cross-reference every behavioral requirement from {ux_content} and {prd_content} against the story's ACs. If a spec requirement has no matching AC, it WILL be silently skipped during implementation.\n   172ŌåÆ- **Implementation-only ACs:** ACs that describe code artifacts (\"function exists\", \"module exports X\") instead of observable behavior (\"user sees X\", \"terminal displays Y\"). These pass verification without proving the feature works.\n   173ŌåÆ- **Narrow ACs that miss the spec's intent:** An AC like \"header shows story key\" technically passes even if the spec says \"header shows story key, phase, elapsed time, and progress counts.\" ACs must cover the FULL expected behavior described in the spec, not just one element of it.\n   174ŌåÆ\n   175ŌåÆ### **Step 4: LLM-Dev-Agent Optimization Analysis**\n   176ŌåÆ\n   177ŌåÆ**CRITICAL STEP: Optimize story context for LLM developer agent consumption**\n   178ŌåÆ\n   179ŌåÆ**Analyze current story for LLM optimization issues:**\n   180ŌåÆ\n   181ŌåÆ- **Verbosity problems:** Excessive detail that wastes tokens without adding value\n   182ŌåÆ- **Ambiguity issues:** Vague instructions that could lead to multiple interpretations\n   183ŌåÆ- **Context overload:** Too much information not directly relevant to implementation\n   184ŌåÆ- **Missing critical signals:** Key requirements buried in verbose text\n   185ŌåÆ- **Poor structure:** Information not organized for efficient LLM processing\n   186ŌåÆ\n   187ŌåÆ**Apply LLM Optimization Principles:**\n   188ŌåÆ\n   189ŌåÆ- **Clarity over verbosity:** Be precise and direct, eliminate fluff\n   190ŌåÆ- **Actionable instructions:** Every sentence should guide implementation\n   191ŌåÆ- **Scannable structure:** Use clear headings, bullet points, and emphasis\n   192ŌåÆ- **Token efficiency:** Pack maximum information into minimum text\n   193ŌåÆ- **Unambiguous language:** Clear requirements with no room for interpretation\n   194ŌåÆ\n   195ŌåÆ### **Step 5: Improvement Recommendations**\n   196ŌåÆ\n   197ŌåÆ**For each gap identified, provide specific, actionable improvements:**\n   198ŌåÆ\n   199ŌåÆ#### **5.1 Critical Misses (Must Fix)**\n   200ŌåÆ\n   201ŌåÆ- Missing essential technical requirements\n   202ŌåÆ- Missing previous story context that could cause errors\n   203ŌåÆ- Missing anti-pattern prevention that could lead to duplicate code\n   204ŌåÆ- Missing security or performance requirements\n   205ŌåÆ\n   206ŌåÆ#### **5.2 Enhancement Opportunities (Should Add)**\n   207ŌåÆ\n   208ŌåÆ- Additional architectural guidance that would help developer\n   209ŌåÆ- More detailed technical specifications\n   210ŌåÆ- Better code reuse opportunities\n   211ŌåÆ- Enhanced testing guidance\n   212ŌåÆ\n   213ŌåÆ#### **5.3 Optimization Suggestions (Nice to Have)**\n   214ŌåÆ\n   215ŌåÆ- Performance optimization hints\n   216ŌåÆ- Additional context for complex scenarios\n   217ŌåÆ- Enhanced debugging or development tips\n   218ŌåÆ\n   219ŌåÆ#### **5.4 LLM Optimization Improvements**\n   220ŌåÆ\n   221ŌåÆ- Token-efficient phrasing of existing content\n   222ŌåÆ- Clearer structure for LLM processing\n   223ŌåÆ- More actionable and direct instructions\n   224ŌåÆ- Reduced verbosity while maintaining completeness\n   225ŌåÆ\n   226ŌåÆ---\n   227ŌåÆ\n   228ŌåÆ## **­¤Ä» COMPETITION SUCCESS METRICS**\n   229ŌåÆ\n   230ŌåÆ**You WIN against the original LLM if you identify:**\n   231ŌåÆ\n   232ŌåÆ### **Category 1: Critical Misses (Blockers)**\n   233ŌåÆ\n   234ŌåÆ- Essential technical requirements the developer needs but aren't provided\n   235ŌåÆ- Previous story learnings that would prevent errors if ignored\n   236ŌåÆ- Anti-pattern prevention that would prevent code duplication\n   237ŌåÆ- Security or performance requirements that must be followed\n   238ŌåÆ\n   239ŌåÆ### **Category 2: Enhancement Opportunities**\n   240ŌåÆ\n   241ŌåÆ- Architecture guidance that would significantly help implementation\n   242ŌåÆ- Technical specifications that would prevent wrong approaches\n   243ŌåÆ- Code reuse opportunities the developer should know about\n   244ŌåÆ- Testing guidance that would improve quality\n   245ŌåÆ\n   246ŌåÆ### **Category 3: Optimization Insights**\n   247ŌåÆ\n   248ŌåÆ- Performance or efficiency improvements\n   249ŌåÆ- Development workflow optimizations\n   250ŌåÆ- Additional context for complex scenarios\n   251ŌåÆ\n   252ŌåÆ---\n   253ŌåÆ\n   254ŌåÆ## **­¤ōŗ INTERACTIVE IMPROVEMENT PROCESS**\n   255ŌåÆ\n   256ŌåÆAfter completing your systematic analysis, present your findings to the user interactively:\n   257ŌåÆ\n   258ŌåÆ### **Step 5: Present Improvement Suggestions**\n   259ŌåÆ\n   260ŌåÆ```\n   261ŌåÆ­¤Ä» **STORY CONTEXT QUALITY REVIEW COMPLETE**\n   262ŌåÆ\n   263ŌåÆ**Story:** {{story_key}} - {{story_title}}\n   264ŌåÆ\n   265ŌåÆI found {{critical_count}} critical issues, {{enhancement_count}} enhancements, and {{optimization_count}} optimizations.\n   266ŌåÆ\n   267ŌåÆ## **­¤Ü© CRITICAL ISSUES (Must Fix)**\n   268ŌåÆ\n   269ŌåÆ{{list each critical issue with clear, actionable description}}\n   270ŌåÆ\n   271ŌåÆ## **ŌÜĪ ENHANCEMENT OPPORTUNITIES (Should Add)**\n   272ŌåÆ\n   273ŌåÆ{{list each enhancement with clear benefit description}}\n   274ŌåÆ\n   275ŌåÆ## **Ō£© OPTIMIZATIONS (Nice to Have)**\n   276ŌåÆ\n   277ŌåÆ{{list each optimization with benefit description}}\n   278ŌåÆ\n   279ŌåÆ## **­¤ż¢ LLM OPTIMIZATION (Token Efficiency & Clarity)**\n   280ŌåÆ\n   281ŌåÆ{{list each LLM optimization that will improve dev agent performance:\n   282ŌåÆ- Reduce verbosity while maintaining completeness\n   283ŌåÆ- Improve structure for better LLM processing\n   284ŌåÆ- Make instructions more actionable and direct\n   285ŌåÆ- Enhance clarity and reduce ambiguity}}\n   286ŌåÆ```\n   287ŌåÆ\n   288ŌåÆ### **Step 6: Interactive User Selection**\n   289ŌåÆ\n   290ŌåÆAfter presenting the suggestions, ask the user:\n   291ŌåÆ\n   292ŌåÆ```\n   293ŌåÆ**IMPROVEMENT OPTIONS:**\n   294ŌåÆ\n   295ŌåÆWhich improvements would you like me to apply to the story?\n   296ŌåÆ\n   297ŌåÆ**Select from the numbered list above, or choose:**\n   298ŌåÆ- **all** - Apply all suggested improvements\n   299ŌåÆ- **critical** - Apply only critical issues\n   300ŌåÆ- **select** - I'll choose specific numbers\n   301ŌåÆ- **none** - Keep story as-is\n   302ŌåÆ- **details** - Show me more details about any suggestion\n   303ŌåÆ\n   304ŌåÆYour choice:\n   305ŌåÆ```\n   306ŌåÆ\n   307ŌåÆ### **Step 7: Apply Selected Improvements**\n   308ŌåÆ\n   309ŌåÆWhen user accepts improvements:\n   310ŌåÆ\n   311ŌåÆ- **Load the story file**\n   312ŌåÆ- **Apply accepted changes** (make them look natural, as if they were always there)\n   313ŌåÆ- **DO NOT reference** the review process, original LLM, or that changes were \"added\" or \"enhanced\"\n   314ŌåÆ- **Ensure clean, coherent final story** that reads as if it was created perfectly the first time\n   315ŌåÆ\n   316ŌåÆ### **Step 8: Confirmation**\n   317ŌåÆ\n   318ŌåÆAfter applying changes:\n   319ŌåÆ\n   320ŌåÆ```\n   321ŌåÆŌ£ģ **STORY IMPROVEMENTS APPLIED**\n   322ŌåÆ\n   323ŌåÆUpdated {{count}} sections in the story file.\n   324ŌåÆ\n   325ŌåÆThe story now includes comprehensive developer guidance to prevent common implementation issues and ensure flawless execution.\n   326ŌåÆ\n   327ŌåÆ**Next Steps:**\n   328ŌåÆ1. Review the updated story\n   329ŌåÆ2. Run `dev-story` for implementation\n   330ŌåÆ```\n   331ŌåÆ\n   332ŌåÆ---\n   333ŌåÆ\n   334ŌåÆ## **­¤Æ¬ COMPETITIVE EXCELLENCE MINDSET**\n   335ŌåÆ\n   336ŌåÆ**Your goal:** Improve the story file with dev agent needed context that makes flawless implementation inevitable while being optimized for LLM developer agent consumption. Remember the dev agent will ONLY have this file to use.\n   337ŌåÆ\n   338ŌåÆ**Success Criteria:** The LLM developer agent that processes your improved story will have:\n   339ŌåÆ\n   340ŌåÆ- Ō£ģ Clear technical requirements they must follow\n   341ŌåÆ- Ō£ģ Previous work context they can build upon\n   342ŌåÆ- Ō£ģ Anti-pattern prevention to avoid common mistakes\n   343ŌåÆ- Ō£ģ Comprehensive guidance for efficient implementation\n   344ŌåÆ- Ō£ģ **Optimized content structure** for maximum clarity and minimum token waste\n   345ŌåÆ- Ō£ģ **Actionable instructions** with no ambiguity or verbosity\n   346ŌåÆ- Ō£ģ **Efficient information density** - maximum guidance in minimum text\n   347ŌåÆ\n   348ŌåÆ**Every improvement should make it IMPOSSIBLE for the developer to:**\n   349ŌåÆ\n   350ŌåÆ- Reinvent existing solutions\n   351ŌåÆ- Use wrong approaches or libraries\n   352ŌåÆ- Create duplicate functionality\n   353ŌåÆ- Miss critical requirements\n   354ŌåÆ- Make implementation errors\n   355ŌåÆ\n   356ŌåÆ**LLM Optimization Should Make it IMPOSSIBLE for the developer agent to:**\n   357ŌåÆ\n   358ŌåÆ- Misinterpret requirements due to ambiguity\n   359ŌåÆ- Waste tokens on verbose, non-actionable content\n   360ŌåÆ- Struggle to find critical information buried in text\n   361ŌåÆ- Get confused by poor structure or organization\n   362ŌåÆ- Miss key implementation signals due to inefficient communication\n   363ŌåÆ\n   364ŌåÆ**Go create the ultimate developer implementation guide! ­¤ÜĆ**\n   365ŌåÆ"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01SqkcCz91dsjFJacd7fAMKf","session_id":"010b7052-acb2-4a98-9861-0b5f61bbdbf0","uuid":"8608a545-ea39-435a-9868-54b121ff204c","timestamp":"2026-03-24T11:58:50.336Z"}
