{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01YUbSQqHDQGUL36uLiyKQPB","type":"tool_result","content":"   170ŌåÆ\n   171ŌåÆ**Acceptance Criteria:**\n   172ŌåÆ\n   173ŌåÆ**Given** `sprint-state.json` and `sprint-status.yaml` are out of sync\n   174ŌåÆ**When** harness-run Step 1 pre-flight runs `reconcileState()`\n   175ŌåÆ**Then** `sprint-state.json` is authoritative and `sprint-status.yaml` is regenerated\n   176ŌåÆ\n   177ŌåÆ---\n   178ŌåÆ\n   179ŌåÆ## Epic 12: lib/ Restructuring\n   180ŌåÆ\n   181ŌåÆSplit oversized files into domain subdirectories. Move business logic from commands to modules.\n   182ŌåÆ\n   183ŌåÆ### Story 12-1: Split coverage.ts into domain subdirectory\n   184ŌåÆ\n   185ŌåÆAs a developer,\n   186ŌåÆI want coverage logic in `src/lib/coverage/` with files under 300 lines each,\n   187ŌåÆSo that coverage code is maintainable and testable.\n   188ŌåÆ\n   189ŌåÆ**Acceptance Criteria:**\n   190ŌåÆ\n   191ŌåÆ**Given** `src/lib/coverage/` exists\n   192ŌåÆ**When** inspected\n   193ŌåÆ**Then** it contains: `index.ts` (<50 lines, re-exports), `types.ts`, `runner.ts`, `evaluator.ts`, `parser.ts`\n   194ŌåÆ\n   195ŌåÆ**Given** each file in `src/lib/coverage/`\n   196ŌåÆ**When** line count is checked\n   197ŌåÆ**Then** no file exceeds 300 lines\n   198ŌåÆ\n   199ŌåÆ**Given** `parseTestCounts()` in `parser.ts`\n   200ŌåÆ**When** cargo workspace output is mixed with pytest-like output\n   201ŌåÆ**Then** cargo aggregation fires first (ordering guard test exists)\n   202ŌåÆ\n   203ŌåÆ### Story 12-2: Split docker.ts, otlp.ts, beads-sync.ts, doc-health.ts\n   204ŌåÆ\n   205ŌåÆAs a developer,\n   206ŌåÆI want all 832/590/422/378-line files split into domain subdirectories,\n   207ŌåÆSo that the entire codebase respects the 300-line limit.\n   208ŌåÆ\n   209ŌåÆ**Acceptance Criteria:**\n   210ŌåÆ\n   211ŌåÆ**Given** `src/lib/docker/` with `compose.ts`, `health.ts`, `cleanup.ts`\n   212ŌåÆ**And** `src/lib/observability/` with `instrument.ts`, `config.ts`, `backends.ts`\n   213ŌåÆ**And** `src/lib/sync/` with `beads.ts`, `sprint-yaml.ts`, `story-files.ts`\n   214ŌåÆ**When** each file is checked\n   215ŌåÆ**Then** no file exceeds 300 lines\n   216ŌåÆ\n   217ŌåÆ**Given** all splits complete\n   218ŌåÆ**When** `npm test` runs\n   219ŌåÆ**Then** all tests pass with 0 regressions\n   220ŌåÆ\n   221ŌåÆ### Story 12-3: Move business logic from status.ts command to status module\n   222ŌåÆ\n   223ŌåÆAs a developer,\n   224ŌåÆI want `src/commands/status.ts` under 100 lines with logic in `src/modules/status/`,\n   225ŌåÆSo that status logic is testable without command wiring.\n   226ŌåÆ\n   227ŌåÆ**Acceptance Criteria:**\n   228ŌåÆ\n   229ŌåÆ**Given** `src/modules/status/` with `index.ts`, `formatters.ts`, `endpoints.ts`, `drill-down.ts`\n   230ŌåÆ**When** `src/commands/status.ts` is inspected\n   231ŌåÆ**Then** it's under 100 lines ŌĆö just arg parsing, module call, output formatting\n   232ŌåÆ\n   233ŌåÆ**Given** `src/modules/status/endpoints.ts`\n   234ŌåÆ**When** `buildScopedEndpoints()` is called\n   235ŌåÆ**Then** it produces the same URLs as the current `status.ts` implementation\n   236ŌåÆ\n   237ŌåÆ### Story 12-4: Shared test utilities and fixtures\n   238ŌåÆ\n   239ŌåÆAs a developer,\n   240ŌåÆI want reusable test helpers and fixtures,\n   241ŌåÆSo that tests don't duplicate mock setup across 50+ files.\n   242ŌåÆ\n   243ŌåÆ**Acceptance Criteria:**\n   244ŌåÆ\n   245ŌåÆ**Given** `src/lib/__tests__/fixtures/` exists\n   246ŌåÆ**When** inspected\n   247ŌåÆ**Then** it contains: `cargo-toml-variants.ts`, `state-builders.ts`, `mock-factories.ts`\n   248ŌåÆ\n   249ŌåÆ**Given** `src/lib/__tests__/helpers.ts` exists\n   250ŌåÆ**When** test files import from it\n   251ŌåÆ**Then** common patterns (mock Docker, mock fs, create temp state) are one-liners\n   252ŌåÆ\n   253ŌåÆ---\n   254ŌåÆ\n   255ŌåÆ## Epic 13: Agent Abstraction\n   256ŌåÆ\n   257ŌåÆRalph behind an AgentDriver interface.\n   258ŌåÆ\n   259ŌåÆ### Story 13-1: Create AgentDriver interface and types\n   260ŌåÆ\n   261ŌåÆAs a developer,\n   262ŌåÆI want an `AgentDriver` interface that abstracts agent execution,\n   263ŌåÆSo that Ralph can be replaced or supplemented without touching 28 files.\n   264ŌåÆ\n   265ŌåÆ**Acceptance Criteria:**\n   266ŌåÆ\n   267ŌåÆ**Given** `src/lib/agents/types.ts` exists\n   268ŌåÆ**When** inspected\n   269ŌåÆ**Then** it defines `AgentDriver`, `AgentProcess`, `AgentEvent` types\n   270ŌåÆ\n   271ŌåÆ**Given** the `AgentEvent` type\n   272ŌåÆ**When** inspected\n   273ŌåÆ**Then** it covers: `tool-start`, `tool-complete`, `text`, `story-complete`, `story-failed`, `iteration`, `retry`, `result`\n   274ŌåÆ\n   275ŌåÆ### Story 13-2: Implement RalphDriver\n   276ŌåÆ\n   277ŌåÆAs a developer,\n   278ŌåÆI want Ralph wrapped in an `AgentDriver` implementation,\n   279ŌåÆSo that ralph-specific behavior is isolated in one file.\n   280ŌåÆ\n   281ŌåÆ**Acceptance Criteria:**\n   282ŌåÆ\n   283ŌåÆ**Given** `src/lib/agents/ralph.ts` exists\n   284ŌåÆ**When** inspected\n   285ŌåÆ**Then** it implements `AgentDriver` with: `spawn()` (builds ralph.sh args), `parseOutput()` (parses ralph stderr + stream-json)\n   286ŌåÆ\n   287ŌåÆ**Given** `run-helpers.ts` ralph-specific functions (`parseRalphMessage`, `parseIterationMessage`, `buildSpawnArgs`)\n   288ŌåÆ**When** migration completes\n   289ŌåÆ**Then** they're moved into `ralph.ts` and `run-helpers.ts` is deleted"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01SqkcCz91dsjFJacd7fAMKf","session_id":"010b7052-acb2-4a98-9861-0b5f61bbdbf0","uuid":"5e191fc6-0f92-46ef-9652-bb46fd1f3ae7","timestamp":"2026-03-24T11:59:07.263Z"}
