st that flags internal cross-domain imports.\n--\n497-Each `StackProvider` provides its verify Dockerfile section:\n498-- **Rust:** Install rustup + stable toolchain + cargo-tarpaulin + clippy + system libs\n499-- **Node.js:** Install Node.js + npm\n500:- **Python:** Install pip + coverage\n501-\n502-The Dockerfile is generated at `verify-env build` time, not selected from a static file. This ensures it always matches the project's needs.\n503-\n--\n552-|------|-------|-----------|\n553-| `doc-health.ts` | 832 | `doc-health/scanner.ts`, `doc-health/staleness.ts`, `doc-health/report.ts` |\n554-| `status.ts` (command) | 744 | Move logic to `modules/status/` |\n555:| `coverage.ts` | 617 | `coverage/runner.ts`, `coverage/evaluator.ts`, `coverage/parser.ts` |\n556-| `beads-sync.ts` | 590 | `sync/beads.ts`, `sync/sprint-yaml.ts`, `sync/story-files.ts` |\n557-| `bmad.ts` | 522 | `sync/bmad-bridge.ts`, `sync/epic-generator.ts` |\n558:| `scanner.ts` | 447 | `scanner/file-scanner.ts`, `scanner/coverage-scanner.ts` |\n559-| `otlp.ts` | 422 | `observability/instrument.ts`, `observability/config.ts` |\n560-\n561----\n--\n570-Ōöé   Ōö£ŌöĆŌöĆ status.ts\n571-Ōöé   Ōö£ŌöĆŌöĆ audit.ts\n572-Ōöé   Ōö£ŌöĆŌöĆ verify.ts\n573:Ōöé   Ōö£ŌöĆŌöĆ coverage.ts\n574-Ōöé   Ōö£ŌöĆŌöĆ stack.ts\n575-Ōöé   ŌööŌöĆŌöĆ ...\n576-Ōö£ŌöĆŌöĆ lib/                # Shared utilities (domain subdirectories)\n577-Ōöé   Ōö£ŌöĆŌöĆ stacks/         # Stack provider pattern (Decision 2)\n578-Ōöé   Ōö£ŌöĆŌöĆ agents/         # Agent driver pattern (Decision 3)\n579:Ōöé   Ōö£ŌöĆŌöĆ coverage/       # Coverage detection, execution, parsing\n580-Ōöé   Ōö£ŌöĆŌöĆ docker/         # Docker compose, health, cleanup\n581-Ōöé   Ōö£ŌöĆŌöĆ observability/  # OTLP instrumentation, backend queries\n582-Ōöé   Ōö£ŌöĆŌöĆ sync/           # Beads, sprint YAML, story files\n--\n671-\n672-```typescript\n673-const provider = getStackProvider(stack);\n674:const coverage = provider.detectCoverageConfig(dir);\n675-const dockerfile = provider.getDo