{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_012nLfAKtWZxjfHR6KNF2qyR","type":"tool_result","content":"     1ŌåÆ# Story 11-3: State Reconciliation on Session Start\n     2ŌåÆ<!-- verification-tier: unit-testable -->\n     3ŌåÆ\n     4ŌåÆ## Status: verifying\n     5ŌåÆ\n     6ŌåÆ## Story\n     7ŌåÆ\n     8ŌåÆAs a developer,\n     9ŌåÆI want state consistency verified at the start of every session,\n    10ŌåÆSo that desyncs from crashes or manual edits are caught immediately.\n    11ŌåÆ\n    12ŌåÆ## Acceptance Criteria\n    13ŌåÆ\n    14ŌåÆ- [x] AC1: Given `sprint-state.json` and `sprint-status.yaml` are out of sync (e.g., a story status was manually edited in the YAML), when harness-run Step 1 pre-flight calls `reconcileState()`, then `sprint-state.json` is treated as authoritative and `sprint-status.yaml` is regenerated from it <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    15ŌåÆ- [x] AC2: Given `sprint-state.json` has no `version` field (legacy v1 state), when `reconcileState()` runs, then it triggers the v1-to-v2 migration from story 11-1 before proceeding with reconciliation <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    16ŌåÆ- [x] AC3: Given orphaned `ralph/.story_retries` file exists with entries already migrated into `sprint-state.json` retries field, when `reconcileState()` runs, then it merges any new entries from the file into `state.retries` and deletes the file <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    17ŌåÆ- [x] AC4: Given orphaned `ralph/.flagged_stories` file exists with entries already migrated into `sprint-state.json` flagged field, when `reconcileState()` runs, then it merges any new entries from the file into `state.flagged` (deduplicating) and deletes the file <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    18ŌåÆ- [x] AC5: Given every story in `state.stories` has a key with an epic prefix (e.g., `11-3-...`), when `reconcileState()` validates internal consistency, then every story's epic prefix corresponds to an epic entry in `state.epics`, and missing epic entries are auto-created with computed status <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    19ŌåÆ- [x] AC6: Given `reconcileState()` made corrections (YAML regeneration, file merges, epic creation), when it completes, then it logs each correction as `[INFO] Reconciled: <description>` (e.g., `[INFO] Reconciled: regenerated sprint-status.yaml`, `[INFO] Reconciled: merged .story_retries into sprint-state.json`) <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    20ŌåÆ- [x] AC7: Given `sprint-state.json` is fully consistent and no orphaned files exist, when `reconcileState()` runs, then it performs no writes and returns without logging any corrections (idempotent no-op) <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    21ŌåÆ- [x] AC8: Given `src/commands/run.ts` Step 1 pre-flight section, when inspected, then `reconcileState()` is called before story selection (before the current step that reads sprint statuses) <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    22ŌåÆ- [x] AC9: Given `src/modules/sprint/__tests__/reconciliation.test.ts` exists, when the test suite runs, then it covers: (a) out-of-sync YAML gets regenerated, (b) orphaned `.story_retries` merged and deleted, (c) orphaned `.flagged_stories` merged and deleted, (d) missing epic entries auto-created, (e) consistent state produces no-op, (f) v1 state triggers migration first <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    23ŌåÆ- [x] AC10: Given `npm test` is run after all changes, when it completes, then all tests pass with 0 regressions <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    24ŌåÆ- [x] AC11: Given `npx tsc --noEmit` is run after all changes, when it completes, then zero new type errors are introduced <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    25ŌåÆ- [x] AC12: Given `reconcileState()` is called during `harness-run` Step 1 pre-flight, when a user has manually edited `sprint-status.yaml` during a session break, then their YAML changes are overwritten because `sprint-state.json` is the single source of truth <!-- verification: integration-required -->\n    26ŌåÆ\n    27ŌåÆ## Tasks/Subtasks\n    28ŌåÆ\n    29ŌåÆ- [x] Task 1: Create `reconcileState()` in `src/modules/sprint/state.ts` ŌĆö The function should: (1) call `getSprintState()` to read current state (which already handles v1-to-v2 migration), (2) check for and merge orphaned `.story_retries` file into `state.retries` then delete the file, (3) check for and merge orphaned `.flagged_stories` file into `state.flagged` then delete the file, (4) validate epic consistency ŌĆö for each story key, parse the epic prefix and ensure a matching epic exists in `state.epics`, creating any missing entries with computed status, (5) regenerate `sprint-status.yaml` unconditionally, (6) write state atomically only if mutations were made, (7) return a list of corrections made (for logging).\n    30ŌåÆ- [x] Task 2: Create a `ReconciliationResult` type ŌĆö with fields `corrections: string[]` and `stateChanged: boolean` to communicate what happened to callers.\n    31ŌåÆ- [x] Task 3: Wire `reconcileState()` into `src/commands/run.ts` Step 1 pre-flight ŌĆö Call it after resolving the Ralph path and plugin directory but before reading sprint statuses for story count. Log each correction from the result. If reconciliation fails, log a warning but do not abort the run (best-effort).\n    32ŌåÆ- [x] Task 4: Export `reconcileState` from `src/modules/sprint/index.ts` ŌĆö Add import and re-export.\n    33ŌåÆ- [x] Task 5: Create `src/modules/sprint/__tests__/reconciliation.test.ts` ŌĆö Test cases: (a) YAML regeneration on desync, (b) orphaned `.story_retries` file merged and deleted, (c) orphaned `.flagged_stories` file merged and deleted, (d) missing epic entries auto-created from story prefixes, (e) already-consistent state is a no-op (no writes), (f) state without `version` field triggers migration, (g) malformed orphan files handled gracefully without crashing.\n    34ŌåÆ- [x] Task 6: Run `npm test` and `npx tsc --noEmit` to verify zero regressions.\n    35ŌåÆ\n    36ŌåÆ## Technical Notes\n    37ŌåÆ\n    38ŌåÆ**Architecture Decision 1 (Unified State)** and **Decision 11 (Process Enforcement)** ŌĆö state reconciliation is one of the embedded gates in harness-run Step 1 pre-flight.\n    39ŌåÆ\n    40ŌåÆ### reconcileState() algorithm\n    41ŌåÆ\n    42ŌåÆ```\n    43ŌåÆfunction reconcileState(): Result<ReconciliationResult>\n    44ŌåÆ  1. state = getSprintState()          // handles v1ŌåÆv2 migration internally\n    45ŌåÆ  2. corrections = []\n    46ŌåÆ  3. changed = false\n    47ŌåÆ\n    48ŌåÆ  // Merge orphaned retry file\n    49ŌåÆ  4. if ralph/.story_retries exists:\n    50ŌåÆ       parse entries\n    51ŌåÆ       for each (key, count) where count > (state.retries[key] ?? 0):\n    52ŌåÆ         state.retries[key] = count\n    53ŌåÆ         changed = true\n    54ŌåÆ       delete ralph/.story_retries\n    55ŌåÆ       corrections.push(\"merged .story_retries into sprint-state.json\")\n    56ŌåÆ\n    57ŌåÆ  // Merge orphaned flagged file\n    58ŌåÆ  5. if ralph/.flagged_stories exists:\n    59ŌåÆ       parse keys\n    60ŌåÆ       for each key not in state.flagged:"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01SqkcCz91dsjFJacd7fAMKf","session_id":"010b7052-acb2-4a98-9861-0b5f61bbdbf0","uuid":"61825365-52a5-4c6a-b560-985953cb8aa3","timestamp":"2026-03-24T11:59:34.110Z"}
