{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_011ELMWch8V22f1bkC3itzsB","type":"tool_result","content":"     1ŌåÆ<workflow>\n     2ŌåÆ  <critical>The workflow execution engine is governed by: {project-root}/_bmad/core/tasks/workflow.xml</critical>\n     3ŌåÆ  <critical>You MUST have already loaded and processed: {installed_path}/workflow.yaml</critical>\n     4ŌåÆ  <critical>Communicate all responses in {communication_language} and language MUST be tailored to {user_skill_level}</critical>\n     5ŌåÆ  <critical>Generate all documents in {document_output_language}</critical>\n     6ŌåÆ  <critical>Only modify the story file in these areas: Tasks/Subtasks checkboxes, Dev Agent Record (Debug Log, Completion Notes), File List,\n     7ŌåÆ    Change Log, and Status</critical>\n     8ŌåÆ  <critical>Execute ALL steps in exact order; do NOT skip steps</critical>\n     9ŌåÆ  <critical>Absolutely DO NOT stop because of \"milestones\", \"significant progress\", or \"session boundaries\". Continue in a single execution\n    10ŌåÆ    until the story is COMPLETE (all ACs satisfied and all tasks/subtasks checked) UNLESS a HALT condition is triggered or the USER gives\n    11ŌåÆ    other instruction.</critical>\n    12ŌåÆ  <critical>Do NOT schedule a \"next session\" or request review pauses unless a HALT condition applies. Only Step 6 decides completion.</critical>\n    13ŌåÆ  <critical>User skill level ({user_skill_level}) affects conversation style ONLY, not code updates.</critical>\n    14ŌåÆ\n    15ŌåÆ  <step n=\"1\" goal=\"Find next ready story and load it\" tag=\"sprint-status\">\n    16ŌåÆ    <check if=\"{{story_path}} is provided\">\n    17ŌåÆ      <action>Use {{story_path}} directly</action>\n    18ŌåÆ      <action>Read COMPLETE story file</action>\n    19ŌåÆ      <action>Extract story_key from filename or metadata</action>\n    20ŌåÆ      <goto anchor=\"task_check\" />\n    21ŌåÆ    </check>\n    22ŌåÆ\n    23ŌåÆ    <!-- Sprint-based story discovery -->\n    24ŌåÆ    <check if=\"{{sprint_status}} file exists\">\n    25ŌåÆ      <critical>MUST read COMPLETE sprint-status.yaml file from start to end to preserve order</critical>\n    26ŌåÆ      <action>Load the FULL file: {{sprint_status}}</action>\n    27ŌåÆ      <action>Read ALL lines from beginning to end - do not skip any content</action>\n    28ŌåÆ      <action>Parse the development_status section completely to understand story order</action>\n    29ŌåÆ\n    30ŌåÆ      <action>Find the FIRST story (by reading in order from top to bottom) where:\n    31ŌåÆ        - Key matches pattern: number-number-name (e.g., \"1-2-user-auth\")\n    32ŌåÆ        - NOT an epic key (epic-X) or retrospective (epic-X-retrospective)\n    33ŌåÆ        - Status value equals \"ready-for-dev\"\n    34ŌåÆ      </action>\n    35ŌåÆ\n    36ŌåÆ      <check if=\"no ready-for-dev or in-progress story found\">\n    37ŌåÆ        <output>­¤ōŗ No ready-for-dev stories found in sprint-status.yaml\n    38ŌåÆ\n    39ŌåÆ          **Current Sprint Status:** {{sprint_status_summary}}\n    40ŌåÆ\n    41ŌåÆ          **What would you like to do?**\n    42ŌåÆ          1. Run `create-story` to create next story from epics with comprehensive context\n    43ŌåÆ          2. Run `*validate-create-story` to improve existing stories before development (recommended quality check)\n    44ŌåÆ          3. Specify a particular story file to develop (provide full path)\n    45ŌåÆ          4. Check {{sprint_status}} file to see current sprint status\n    46ŌåÆ\n    47ŌåÆ          ­¤ÆĪ **Tip:** Stories in `ready-for-dev` may not have been validated. Consider running `validate-create-story` first for a quality\n    48ŌåÆ          check.\n    49ŌåÆ        </output>\n    50ŌåÆ        <ask>Choose option [1], [2], [3], or [4], or specify story file path:</ask>\n    51ŌåÆ\n    52ŌåÆ        <check if=\"user chooses '1'\">\n    53ŌåÆ          <action>HALT - Run create-story to create next story</action>\n    54ŌåÆ        </check>\n    55ŌåÆ\n    56ŌåÆ        <check if=\"user chooses '2'\">\n    57ŌåÆ          <action>HALT - Run validate-create-story to improve existing stories</action>\n    58ŌåÆ        </check>\n    59ŌåÆ\n    60ŌåÆ        <check if=\"user chooses '3'\">\n    61ŌåÆ          <ask>Provide the story file path to develop:</ask>\n    62ŌåÆ          <action>Store user-provided story path as {{story_path}}</action>\n    63ŌåÆ          <goto anchor=\"task_check\" />\n    64ŌåÆ        </check>\n    65ŌåÆ\n    66ŌåÆ        <check if=\"user chooses '4'\">\n    67ŌåÆ          <output>Loading {{sprint_status}} for detailed status review...</output>\n    68ŌåÆ          <action>Display detailed sprint status analysis</action>\n    69ŌåÆ          <action>HALT - User can review sprint status and provide story path</action>\n    70ŌåÆ        </check>\n    71ŌåÆ\n    72ŌåÆ        <check if=\"user provides story file path\">\n    73ŌåÆ          <action>Store user-provided story path as {{story_path}}</action>\n    74ŌåÆ          <goto anchor=\"task_check\" />\n    75ŌåÆ        </check>\n    76ŌåÆ      </check>\n    77ŌåÆ    </check>\n    78ŌåÆ\n    79ŌåÆ    <!-- Non-sprint story discovery -->\n    80ŌåÆ    <check if=\"{{sprint_status}} file does NOT exist\">\n    81ŌåÆ      <action>Search {implementation_artifacts} for stories directly</action>\n    82ŌåÆ      <action>Find stories with \"ready-for-dev\" status in files</action>\n    83ŌåÆ      <action>Look for story files matching pattern: *-*-*.md</action>\n    84ŌåÆ      <action>Read each candidate story file to check Status section</action>\n    85ŌåÆ\n    86ŌåÆ      <check if=\"no ready-for-dev stories found in story files\">\n    87ŌåÆ        <output>­¤ōŗ No ready-for-dev stories found\n    88ŌåÆ\n    89ŌåÆ          **Available Options:**\n    90ŌåÆ          1. Run `create-story` to create next story from epics with comprehensive context\n    91ŌåÆ          2. Run `*validate-create-story` to improve existing stories\n    92ŌåÆ          3. Specify which story to develop\n    93ŌåÆ        </output>\n    94ŌåÆ        <ask>What would you like to do? Choose option [1], [2], or [3]:</ask>\n    95ŌåÆ\n    96ŌåÆ        <check if=\"user chooses '1'\">\n    97ŌåÆ          <action>HALT - Run create-story to create next story</action>\n    98ŌåÆ        </check>\n    99ŌåÆ\n   100ŌåÆ        <check if=\"user chooses '2'\">\n   101ŌåÆ          <action>HALT - Run validate-create-story to improve existing stories</action>\n   102ŌåÆ        </check>\n   103ŌåÆ\n   104ŌåÆ        <check if=\"user chooses '3'\">\n   105ŌåÆ          <ask>It's unclear what story you want developed. Please provide the full path to the story file:</ask>\n   106ŌåÆ          <action>Store user-provided story path as {{story_path}}</action>\n   107ŌåÆ          <action>Continue with provided story file</action>\n   108ŌåÆ        </check>\n   109ŌåÆ      </check>\n   110ŌåÆ\n   111ŌåÆ      <check if=\"ready-for-dev story found in files\">\n   112ŌåÆ        <action>Use discovered story file and extract story_key</action>\n   113ŌåÆ      </check>\n   114ŌåÆ    </check>\n   115ŌåÆ\n   116ŌåÆ    <action>Store the found story_key (e.g., \"1-2-user-authentication\") for later status updates</action>\n   117ŌåÆ    <action>Find matching story file in {implementation_artifacts} using story_key pattern: {{story_key}}.md</action>\n   118ŌåÆ    <action>Read COMPLETE story file from discovered path</action>\n   119ŌåÆ\n   120ŌåÆ    <anchor id=\"task_check\" />\n   121ŌåÆ\n   122ŌåÆ    <action>Parse sections: Story, Acceptance Criteria, Tasks/Subtasks, Dev Notes, Dev Agent Record, File List, Change Log, Status</action>\n   123ŌåÆ\n   124ŌåÆ    <action>Load comprehensive context from story file's Dev Notes section</action>\n   125ŌåÆ    <action>Extract developer guidance from Dev Notes: architecture requirements, previous learnings, technical specifications</action>\n   126ŌåÆ    <action>Use enhanced story context to inform implementation decisions and approaches</action>\n   127ŌåÆ\n   128ŌåÆ    <action>Identify first incomplete task (unchecked [ ]) in Tasks/Subtasks</action>\n   129ŌåÆ\n   130ŌåÆ    <action if=\"no incomplete tasks\">\n   131ŌåÆ      <goto step=\"6\">Completion sequence</goto>\n   132ŌåÆ    </action>\n   133ŌåÆ    <action if=\"story file inaccessible\">HALT: \"Cannot develop story without access to story file\"</action>\n   134ŌåÆ    <action if=\"incomplete task or subtask requirements ambiguous\">ASK user to clarify or HALT</action>\n   135ŌåÆ  </step>\n   136ŌåÆ\n   137ŌåÆ  <step n=\"2\" goal=\"Load project context and story information\">\n   138ŌåÆ    <critical>Load all available context to inform implementation</critical>\n   139ŌåÆ\n   140ŌåÆ    <action>Load {project_context} for coding standards and project-wide patterns (if exists)</action>\n   141ŌåÆ    <action>Parse sections: Story, Acceptance Criteria, Tasks/Subtasks, Dev Notes, Dev Agent Record, File List, Change Log, Status</action>\n   142ŌåÆ    <action>Load comprehensive context from story file's Dev Notes section</action>\n   143ŌåÆ    <action>Extract developer guidance from Dev Notes: architecture requirements, previous learnings, technical specifications</action>\n   144ŌåÆ    <action>Use enhanced story context to inform implementation decisions and approaches</action>\n   145ŌåÆ    <output>Ō£ģ **Context Loaded**\n   146ŌåÆ      Story and project context available for implementation\n   147ŌåÆ    </output>\n   148ŌåÆ  </step>\n   149ŌåÆ\n   150ŌåÆ  <step n=\"3\" goal=\"Detect review continuation and extract review context\">\n   151ŌåÆ    <critical>Determine if this is a fresh start or continuation after code review</critical>\n   152ŌåÆ\n   153ŌåÆ    <action>Check if \"Senior Developer Review (AI)\" section exists in the story file</action>\n   154ŌåÆ    <action>Check if \"Review Follow-ups (AI)\" subsection exists under Tasks/Subtasks</action>\n   155ŌåÆ\n   156ŌåÆ    <check if=\"Senior Developer Review section exists\">\n   157ŌåÆ      <action>Set review_continuation = true</action>\n   158ŌåÆ      <action>Extract from \"Senior Developer Review (AI)\" section:\n   159ŌåÆ        - Review outcome (Approve/Changes Requested/Blocked)\n   160ŌåÆ        - Review date\n   161ŌåÆ        - Total action items with checkboxes (count checked vs unchecked)\n   162ŌåÆ        - Severity breakdown (High/Med/Low counts)\n   163ŌåÆ      </action>\n   164ŌåÆ      <action>Count unchecked [ ] review follow-up tasks in \"Review Follow-ups (AI)\" subsection</action>\n   165ŌåÆ      <action>Store list of unchecked review items as {{pending_review_items}}</action>\n   166ŌåÆ\n   167ŌåÆ      <output>ŌÅ»’ĖÅ **Resuming Story After Code Review** ({{review_date}})\n   168ŌåÆ\n   169ŌåÆ        **Review Outcome:** {{review_outcome}}\n   170ŌåÆ        **Action Items:** {{unchecked_review_count}} remaining to address\n   171ŌåÆ        **Priorities:** {{high_count}} High, {{med_count}} Medium, {{low_count}} Low\n   172ŌåÆ\n   173ŌåÆ        **Strategy:** Will prioritize review follow-up tasks (marked [AI-Review]) before continuing with regular tasks.\n   174ŌåÆ      </output>\n   175ŌåÆ    </check>\n   176ŌåÆ\n   177ŌåÆ    <check if=\"Senior Developer Review section does NOT exist\">\n   178ŌåÆ      <action>Set review_continuation = false</action>\n   179ŌåÆ      <action>Set {{pending_review_items}} = empty</action>\n   180ŌåÆ\n   181ŌåÆ      <output>­¤ÜĆ **Starting Fresh Implementation**\n   182ŌåÆ\n   183ŌåÆ        Story: {{story_key}}\n   184ŌåÆ        Story Status: {{current_status}}\n   185ŌåÆ        First incomplete task: {{first_task_description}}\n   186ŌåÆ      </output>\n   187ŌåÆ    </check>\n   188ŌåÆ  </step>\n   189ŌåÆ\n   190ŌåÆ  <step n=\"4\" goal=\"Mark story in-progress\" tag=\"sprint-status\">\n   191ŌåÆ    <check if=\"{{sprint_status}} file exists\">\n   192ŌåÆ      <action>Load the FULL file: {{sprint_status}}</action>\n   193ŌåÆ      <action>Read all development_status entries to find {{story_key}}</action>\n   194ŌåÆ      <action>Get current status value for development_status[{{story_key}}]</action>\n   195ŌåÆ\n   196ŌåÆ      <check if=\"current status == 'ready-for-dev' OR review_continuation == true\">\n   197ŌåÆ        <action>Update the story in the sprint status report to = \"in-progress\"</action>\n   198ŌåÆ        <output>­¤ÜĆ Starting work on story {{story_key}}\n   199ŌåÆ          Status updated: ready-for-dev ŌåÆ in-progress\n   200ŌåÆ        </output>\n   201ŌåÆ      </check>\n   202ŌåÆ\n   203ŌåÆ      <check if=\"current status == 'in-progress'\">\n   204ŌåÆ        <output>ŌÅ»’ĖÅ Resuming work on story {{story_key}}\n   205ŌåÆ          Story is already marked in-progress\n   206ŌåÆ        </output>\n   207ŌåÆ      </check>\n   208ŌåÆ\n   209ŌåÆ      <check if=\"current status is neither ready-for-dev nor in-progress\">\n   210ŌåÆ        <output>ŌÜĀ’ĖÅ Unexpected story status: {{current_status}}\n   211ŌåÆ          Expected ready-for-dev or in-progress. Continuing anyway...\n   212ŌåÆ        </output>\n   213ŌåÆ      </check>\n   214ŌåÆ\n   215ŌåÆ      <action>Store {{current_sprint_status}} for later use</action>\n   216ŌåÆ    </check>\n   217ŌåÆ\n   218ŌåÆ    <check if=\"{{sprint_status}} file does NOT exist\">\n   219ŌåÆ      <output>Ōä╣’ĖÅ No sprint status file exists - story progress will be tracked in story file only</output>\n   220ŌåÆ      <action>Set {{current_sprint_status}} = \"no-sprint-tracking\"</action>\n   221ŌåÆ    </check>\n   222ŌåÆ  </step>\n   223ŌåÆ\n   224ŌåÆ  <step n=\"5\" goal=\"Implement task following red-green-refactor cycle\">\n   225ŌåÆ    <critical>FOLLOW THE STORY FILE TASKS/SUBTASKS SEQUENCE EXACTLY AS WRITTEN - NO DEVIATION</critical>\n   226ŌåÆ\n   227ŌåÆ    <action>Review the current task/subtask from the story file - this is your authoritative implementation guide</action>\n   228ŌåÆ    <action>Plan implementation following red-green-refactor cycle</action>\n   229ŌåÆ\n   230ŌåÆ    <!-- RED PHASE -->\n   231ŌåÆ    <action>Write FAILING tests first for the task/subtask functionality</action>\n   232ŌåÆ    <action>Confirm tests fail before implementation - this validates test correctness</action>\n   233ŌåÆ\n   234ŌåÆ    <!-- GREEN PHASE -->\n   235ŌåÆ    <action>Implement MINIMAL code to make tests pass</action>\n   236ŌåÆ    <action>Run tests to confirm they now pass</action>\n   237ŌåÆ    <action>Handle error conditions and edge cases as specified in task/subtask</action>\n   238ŌåÆ\n   239ŌåÆ    <!-- REFACTOR PHASE -->\n   240ŌåÆ    <action>Improve code structure while keeping tests green</action>\n   241ŌåÆ    <action>Ensure code follows architecture patterns and coding standards from Dev Notes</action>\n   242ŌåÆ\n   243ŌåÆ    <action>Document technical approach and decisions in Dev Agent Record ŌåÆ Implementation Plan</action>\n   244ŌåÆ\n   245ŌåÆ    <action if=\"new dependencies required beyond story specifications\">HALT: \"Additional dependencies need user approval\"</action>\n   246ŌåÆ    <action if=\"3 consecutive implementation failures occur\">HALT and request guidance</action>\n   247ŌåÆ    <action if=\"required configuration is missing\">HALT: \"Cannot proceed without necessary configuration files\"</action>\n   248ŌåÆ\n   249ŌåÆ    <critical>NEVER implement anything not mapped to a specific task/subtask in the story file</critical>\n   250ŌåÆ    <critical>NEVER proceed to next task until current task/subtask is complete AND tests pass</critical>\n   251ŌåÆ    <critical>Execute continuously without pausing until all tasks/subtasks are complete or explicit HALT condition</critical>\n   252ŌåÆ    <critical>Do NOT propose to pause for review until Step 9 completion gates are satisfied</critical>\n   253ŌåÆ  </step>\n   254ŌåÆ\n   255ŌåÆ  <!-- CODEHARNESS-PATCH-START:dev-enforcement -->\n   256ŌåÆ  <step n=\"5.5\" goal=\"Harness enforcement gates\">\n   257ŌåÆ    <critical>Codeharness requires these checks before proceeding to tests</critical>\n   258ŌåÆ    <action>Verify AGENTS.md files are updated for all modules touched during implementation</action>\n   259ŌåÆ    <action>Create or update exec-plan in docs/exec-plans/active/ for this story</action>\n   260ŌåÆ    <action>Ensure all new code has appropriate test stubs before writing full tests</action>\n   261ŌåÆ    <action>Run `codeharness coverage` to execute tests with coverage and set session flags (tests_passed, coverage_met)</action>\n   262ŌåÆ    <action>If codeharness coverage is not installed or fails, fall back to running test suite manually and verify 100% coverage target</action>\n   263ŌåÆ    <action if=\"tests_passed is false\">HALT: \"Tests failed ŌĆö fix tests before continuing\"</action>\n   264ŌåÆ    <action if=\"coverage_met is false\">HALT: \"Coverage target not met ŌĆö add tests before continuing\"</action>\n   265ŌåÆ  </step>\n   266ŌåÆ  <!-- CODEHARNESS-PATCH-END:dev-enforcement -->\n   267ŌåÆ\n   268ŌåÆ  <step n=\"6\" goal=\"Author comprehensive tests\">\n   269ŌåÆ    <action>Create unit tests for business logic and core functionality introduced/changed by the task</action>\n   270ŌåÆ    <action>Add integration tests for component interactions specified in story requirements</action>\n   271ŌåÆ    <action>Include end-to-end tests for critical user flows when story requirements demand them</action>\n   272ŌåÆ    <action>Cover edge cases and error handling scenarios identified in story Dev Notes</action>\n   273ŌåÆ  </step>\n   274ŌåÆ\n   275ŌåÆ  <step n=\"7\" goal=\"Run validations and tests\">\n   276ŌåÆ    <action>Determine how to run tests for this repo (infer test framework from project structure)</action>\n   277ŌåÆ    <action>Run all existing tests to ensure no regressions</action>\n   278ŌåÆ    <action>Run the new tests to verify implementation correctness</action>\n   279ŌåÆ    <action>Run linting and code quality checks if configured in project</action>\n   280ŌåÆ    <action>Validate implementation meets ALL story acceptance criteria; enforce quantitative thresholds explicitly</action>\n   281ŌåÆ    <action if=\"regression tests fail\">STOP and fix before continuing - identify breaking changes immediately</action>\n   282ŌåÆ    <action if=\"new tests fail\">STOP and fix before continuing - ensure implementation correctness</action>\n   283ŌåÆ  </step>\n   284ŌåÆ\n   285ŌåÆ  <step n=\"8\" goal=\"Validate and mark task complete ONLY when fully done\">\n   286ŌåÆ    <critical>NEVER mark a task complete unless ALL conditions are met - NO LYING OR CHEATING</critical>\n   287ŌåÆ\n   288ŌåÆ    <!-- VALIDATION GATES -->\n   289ŌåÆ    <action>Verify ALL tests for this task/subtask ACTUALLY EXIST and PASS 100%</action>\n   290ŌåÆ    <action>Confirm implementation matches EXACTLY what the task/subtask specifies - no extra features</action>\n   291ŌåÆ    <action>Validate that ALL acceptance criteria related to this task are satisfied</action>\n   292ŌåÆ    <action>Run full test suite to ensure NO regressions introduced</action>\n   293ŌåÆ\n   294ŌåÆ    <!-- REVIEW FOLLOW-UP HANDLING -->\n   295ŌåÆ    <check if=\"task is review follow-up (has [AI-Review] prefix)\">\n   296ŌåÆ      <action>Extract review item details (severity, description, related AC/file)</action>\n   297ŌåÆ      <action>Add to resolution tracking list: {{resolved_review_items}}</action>\n   298ŌåÆ\n   299ŌåÆ      <!-- Mark task in Review Follow-ups section -->\n   300ŌåÆ      <action>Mark task checkbox [x] in \"Tasks/Subtasks ŌåÆ Review Follow-ups (AI)\" section</action>\n   301ŌåÆ\n   302ŌåÆ      <!-- CRITICAL: Also mark corresponding action item in review section -->\n   303ŌåÆ      <action>Find matching action item in \"Senior Developer Review (AI) ŌåÆ Action Items\" section by matching description</action>\n   304ŌåÆ      <action>Mark that action item checkbox [x] as resolved</action>\n   305ŌåÆ\n   306ŌåÆ      <action>Add to Dev Agent Record ŌåÆ Completion Notes: \"Ō£ģ Resolved review finding [{{severity}}]: {{description}}\"</action>\n   307ŌåÆ    </check>\n   308ŌåÆ\n   309ŌåÆ    <!-- ONLY MARK COMPLETE IF ALL VALIDATION PASS -->\n   310ŌåÆ    <check if=\"ALL validation gates pass AND tests ACTUALLY exist and pass\">\n   311ŌåÆ      <action>ONLY THEN mark the task (and subtasks) checkbox with [x]</action>\n   312ŌåÆ      <action>Update File List section with ALL new, modified, or deleted files (paths relative to repo root)</action>\n   313ŌåÆ      <action>Add completion notes to Dev Agent Record summarizing what was ACTUALLY implemented and tested</action>\n   314ŌåÆ    </check>\n   315ŌåÆ\n   316ŌåÆ    <check if=\"ANY validation fails\">\n   317ŌåÆ      <action>DO NOT mark task complete - fix issues first</action>\n   318ŌåÆ      <action>HALT if unable to fix validation failures</action>\n   319ŌåÆ    </check>\n   320ŌåÆ\n   321ŌåÆ    <check if=\"review_continuation == true and {{resolved_review_items}} is not empty\">\n   322ŌåÆ      <action>Count total resolved review items in this session</action>\n   323ŌåÆ      <action>Add Change Log entry: \"Addressed code review findings - {{resolved_count}} items resolved (Date: {{date}})\"</action>\n   324ŌåÆ    </check>\n   325ŌåÆ\n   326ŌåÆ    <action>Save the story file</action>\n   327ŌåÆ    <action>Determine if more incomplete tasks remain</action>\n   328ŌåÆ    <action if=\"more tasks remain\">\n   329ŌåÆ      <goto step=\"5\">Next task</goto>\n   330ŌåÆ    </action>\n   331ŌåÆ    <action if=\"no tasks remain\">\n   332ŌåÆ      <goto step=\"9\">Completion</goto>\n   333ŌåÆ    </action>\n   334ŌåÆ  </step>\n   335ŌåÆ\n   336ŌåÆ  <step n=\"9\" goal=\"Story completion and mark for review\" tag=\"sprint-status\">\n   337ŌåÆ    <action>Verify ALL tasks and subtasks are marked [x] (re-scan the story document now)</action>\n   338ŌåÆ    <action>Run the full regression suite (do not skip)</action>\n   339ŌåÆ    <action>Confirm File List includes every changed file</action>\n   340ŌåÆ    <action>Execute enhanced definition-of-done validation</action>\n   341ŌåÆ    <action>Update the story Status to: \"review\"</action>\n   342ŌåÆ\n   343ŌåÆ    <!-- Enhanced Definition of Done Validation -->\n   344ŌåÆ    <action>Validate definition-of-done checklist with essential requirements:\n   345ŌåÆ      - All tasks/subtasks marked complete with [x]\n   346ŌåÆ      - Implementation satisfies every Acceptance Criterion\n   347ŌåÆ      - Unit tests for core functionality added/updated\n   348ŌåÆ      - Integration tests for component interactions added when required\n   349ŌåÆ      - End-to-end tests for critical flows added when story demands them\n   350ŌåÆ      - All tests pass (no regressions, new tests successful)\n   351ŌåÆ      - Code quality checks pass (linting, static analysis if configured)\n   352ŌåÆ      - File List includes every new/modified/deleted file (relative paths)\n   353ŌåÆ      - Dev Agent Record contains implementation notes\n   354ŌåÆ      - Change Log includes summary of changes\n   355ŌåÆ      - Only permitted story sections were modified\n   356ŌåÆ    </action>\n   357ŌåÆ\n   358ŌåÆ    <!-- Mark story ready for review - sprint status conditional -->\n   359ŌåÆ    <check if=\"{sprint_status} file exists AND {{current_sprint_status}} != 'no-sprint-tracking'\">\n   360ŌåÆ      <action>Load the FULL file: {sprint_status}</action>\n   361ŌåÆ      <action>Find development_status key matching {{story_key}}</action>\n   362ŌåÆ      <action>Verify current status is \"in-progress\" (expected previous state)</action>\n   363ŌåÆ      <action>Update development_status[{{story_key}}] = \"review\"</action>\n   364ŌåÆ      <action>Save file, preserving ALL comments and structure including STATUS DEFINITIONS</action>\n   365ŌåÆ      <output>Ō£ģ Story status updated to \"review\" in sprint-status.yaml</output>\n   366ŌåÆ    </check>\n   367ŌåÆ\n   368ŌåÆ    <check if=\"{sprint_status} file does NOT exist OR {{current_sprint_status}} == 'no-sprint-tracking'\">\n   369ŌåÆ      <output>Ōä╣’ĖÅ Story status updated to \"review\" in story file (no sprint tracking configured)</output>\n   370ŌåÆ    </check>\n   371ŌåÆ\n   372ŌåÆ    <check if=\"story key not found in sprint status\">\n   373ŌåÆ      <output>ŌÜĀ’ĖÅ Story file updated, but sprint-status update failed: {{story_key}} not found\n   374ŌåÆ\n   375ŌåÆ        Story status is set to \"review\" in file, but sprint-status.yaml may be out of sync.\n   376ŌåÆ      </output>\n   377ŌåÆ    </check>\n   378ŌåÆ\n   379ŌåÆ    <!-- Final validation gates -->\n   380ŌåÆ    <action if=\"any task is incomplete\">HALT - Complete remaining tasks before marking ready for review</action>\n   381ŌåÆ    <action if=\"regression failures exist\">HALT - Fix regression issues before completing</action>\n   382ŌåÆ    <action if=\"File List is incomplete\">HALT - Update File List with all changed files</action>\n   383ŌåÆ    <action if=\"definition-of-done validation fails\">HALT - Address DoD failures before completing</action>\n   384ŌåÆ  </step>\n   385ŌåÆ\n   386ŌåÆ  <step n=\"10\" goal=\"Completion communication and user support\">\n   387ŌåÆ    <action>Execute the enhanced definition-of-done checklist using the validation framework</action>\n   388ŌåÆ    <action>Prepare a concise summary in Dev Agent Record ŌåÆ Completion Notes</action>\n   389ŌåÆ\n   390ŌåÆ    <action>Communicate to {user_name} that story implementation is complete and ready for review</action>\n   391ŌåÆ    <action>Summarize key accomplishments: story ID, story key, title, key changes made, tests added, files modified</action>\n   392ŌåÆ    <action>Provide the story file path and current status (now \"review\")</action>\n   393ŌåÆ\n   394ŌåÆ    <action>Based on {user_skill_level}, ask if user needs any explanations about:\n   395ŌåÆ      - What was implemented and how it works\n   396ŌåÆ      - Why certain technical decisions were made\n   397ŌåÆ      - How to test or verify the changes\n   398ŌåÆ      - Any patterns, libraries, or approaches used\n   399ŌåÆ      - Anything else they'd like clarified\n   400ŌåÆ    </action>\n   401ŌåÆ\n   402ŌåÆ    <check if=\"user asks for explanations\">\n   403ŌåÆ      <action>Provide clear, contextual explanations tailored to {user_skill_level}</action>\n   404ŌåÆ      <action>Use examples and references to specific code when helpful</action>\n   405ŌåÆ    </check>\n   406ŌåÆ\n   407ŌåÆ    <action>Once explanations are complete (or user indicates no questions), suggest logical next steps</action>\n   408ŌåÆ    <action>Recommended next steps (flexible based on project setup):\n   409ŌåÆ      - Review the implemented story and test the changes\n   410ŌåÆ      - Verify all acceptance criteria are met\n   411ŌåÆ      - Ensure deployment readiness if applicable\n   412ŌåÆ      - Run `code-review` workflow for peer review\n   413ŌåÆ      - Optional: If Test Architect module installed, run `/bmad:tea:automate` to expand guardrail tests\n   414ŌåÆ    </action>\n   415ŌåÆ\n   416ŌåÆ    <output>­¤ÆĪ **Tip:** For best results, run `code-review` using a **different** LLM than the one that implemented this story.</output>\n   417ŌåÆ    <check if=\"{sprint_status} file exists\">\n   418ŌåÆ      <action>Suggest checking {sprint_status} to see project progress</action>\n   419ŌåÆ    </check>\n   420ŌåÆ    <action>Remain flexible - allow user to choose their own path or ask for other assistance</action>\n   421ŌåÆ  </step>\n   422ŌåÆ\n   423ŌåÆ</workflow>\n   424ŌåÆ"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01W89Wqd4iQCSzVpohSh2yqq","session_id":"010b7052-acb2-4a98-9861-0b5f61bbdbf0","uuid":"00009610-ef88-48e0-9072-2d574b041942","timestamp":"2026-03-24T12:04:08.385Z"}
