{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_0169QQgttckrvhL53n6tYQWJ","type":"tool_result","content":"     1ŌåÆ# Story 12.1: Split coverage.ts into domain subdirectory\n     2ŌåÆ\n     3ŌåÆStatus: review\n     4ŌåÆ\n     5ŌåÆ## Story\n     6ŌåÆ\n     7ŌåÆAs a developer,\n     8ŌåÆI want coverage logic in `src/lib/coverage/` with files under 300 lines each,\n     9ŌåÆSo that coverage code is maintainable and testable.\n    10ŌåÆ\n    11ŌåÆ## Acceptance Criteria\n    12ŌåÆ\n    13ŌåÆ1. AC1: Given `src/lib/coverage/` directory exists, when inspected, then it contains: `index.ts` (under 50 lines, re-exports only), `types.ts`, `runner.ts`, `evaluator.ts`, `parser.ts` <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    14ŌåÆ2. AC2: Given each file in `src/lib/coverage/`, when `wc -l` is run on every file, then no file exceeds 300 lines <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    15ŌåÆ3. AC3: Given `parseTestCounts()` lives in `parser.ts`, when cargo workspace output is mixed with pytest-like output, then cargo aggregation fires first (an ordering guard test exists in the test suite) <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    16ŌåÆ4. AC4: Given the old `src/lib/coverage.ts` file, when the split is complete, then it no longer exists (deleted, not left as a stub) <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    17ŌåÆ5. AC5: Given all consumers that previously imported from `../lib/coverage.js` (`src/commands/coverage.ts`, `src/modules/audit/dimensions.ts`, `src/lib/scanner.ts`, `src/lib/onboard-checks.ts`) and their test files, when import paths are inspected, then they import from `../lib/coverage/index.js` (or `../lib/coverage/` which resolves to index) <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    18ŌåÆ6. AC6: Given `src/lib/coverage/index.ts` is inspected, when its contents are reviewed, then it re-exports exactly: `detectCoverageTool`, `getTestCommand`, `runCoverage`, `parseCoverageReport`, `parseTestCounts`, `checkOnlyCoverage`, `evaluateCoverage`, `updateCoverageState`, `checkPerFileCoverage`, `formatCoverageOutput`, `printCoverageOutput`, and all exported types (`CoverageToolInfo`, `CoverageResult`, `CoverageEvaluation`, `FileCoverageEntry`, `PerFileCoverageResult`) <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    19ŌåÆ7. AC7: Given `npm test` is run after all changes, when it completes, then all tests pass with 0 regressions <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    20ŌåÆ8. AC8: Given `npx tsc --noEmit` is run after all changes, when it completes, then zero new type errors are introduced <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    21ŌåÆ9. AC9: Given coverage test file `src/lib/__tests__/coverage.test.ts` (968 lines), when the split is complete, then tests are reorganized under `src/lib/coverage/__tests__/` with files corresponding to the source modules (e.g., `runner.test.ts`, `evaluator.test.ts`, `parser.test.ts`) <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    22ŌåÆ10. AC10: Given `src/lib/coverage/runner.ts` imports from sibling files within `coverage/`, when cross-domain imports are checked, then no file inside `coverage/` imports directly from internal files of another domain directory (e.g., no `import from '../../docker/compose.js'` ŌĆö only through `../../docker/index.js`) <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    23ŌåÆ11. AC11: Given a user runs `codeharness coverage` or `codeharness coverage --check-only`, when the command executes end-to-end, then observable behavior is identical to before the split (same output, same exit codes, same JSON format) <!-- verification: integration-required -->\n    24ŌåÆ\n    25ŌåÆ## Tasks/Subtasks\n    26ŌåÆ\n    27ŌåÆ- [x] Task 1: Create `src/lib/coverage/types.ts` ŌĆö Move all interfaces and type aliases: `CoverageToolInfo`, `CoverageResult`, `CoverageEvaluation`, `FileCoverageEntry`, `PerFileCoverageResult` (AC: #1, #6)\n    28ŌåÆ  - [x] Include any type-only imports needed (e.g., `StackName`)\n    29ŌåÆ- [x] Task 2: Create `src/lib/coverage/parser.ts` ŌĆö Move `parseTestCounts()` and `parseCoverageReport()` (AC: #1, #3)\n    30ŌåÆ  - [x] Ensure cargo aggregation ordering is preserved exactly\n    31ŌåÆ  - [x] Import types from `./types.js`\n    32ŌåÆ- [x] Task 3: Create `src/lib/coverage/runner.ts` ŌĆö Move `detectCoverageTool()`, `getTestCommand()`, `runCoverage()`, `checkOnlyCoverage()`, and all private helpers (coverage detector map, `getStateToolHint`, stack-specific detection functions) (AC: #1)\n    33ŌåÆ  - [x] Import from `./types.js` and `./parser.js`\n    34ŌåÆ  - [x] Import shared utilities from `../state.js`, `../output.js`, `../stacks/index.js`\n    35ŌåÆ- [x] Task 4: Create `src/lib/coverage/evaluator.ts` ŌĆö Move `evaluateCoverage()`, `updateCoverageState()`, `checkPerFileCoverage()`, `formatCoverageOutput()`, `printCoverageOutput()` (AC: #1)\n    36ŌåÆ  - [x] Import from `./types.js`\n    37ŌåÆ  - [x] Import shared utilities from `../state.js`, `../output.js`\n    38ŌåÆ- [x] Task 5: Create `src/lib/coverage/index.ts` ŌĆö Pure re-export barrel file, under 50 lines (AC: #1, #6)\n    39ŌåÆ  - [x] Re-export all public functions and types from `./types.js`, `./runner.js`, `./evaluator.js`, `./parser.js`\n    40ŌåÆ- [x] Task 6: Update all consumer imports (AC: #5)\n    41ŌåÆ  - [x] `src/commands/coverage.ts` ŌĆö `from '../lib/coverage.js'` ŌåÆ `from '../lib/coverage/index.js'`\n    42ŌåÆ  - [x] `src/modules/audit/dimensions.ts` ŌĆö `from '../../lib/coverage.js'` ŌåÆ `from '../../lib/coverage/index.js'`\n    43ŌåÆ  - [x] `src/lib/scanner.ts` ŌĆö `from './coverage.js'` ŌåÆ `from './coverage/index.js'`\n    44ŌåÆ  - [x] `src/lib/onboard-checks.ts` ŌĆö `from './coverage.js'` ŌåÆ `from './coverage/index.js'`\n    45ŌåÆ  - [x] All corresponding test files that import from coverage\n    46ŌåÆ- [x] Task 7: Delete old `src/lib/coverage.ts` (AC: #4)\n    47ŌåÆ- [x] Task 8: Reorganize tests from `src/lib/__tests__/coverage.test.ts` into `src/lib/coverage/__tests__/` (AC: #9)\n    48ŌåÆ  - [x] `parser.test.ts` ŌĆö tests for `parseTestCounts`, `parseCoverageReport`\n    49ŌåÆ  - [x] `runner.test.ts` ŌĆö tests for `detectCoverageTool`, `runCoverage`, `checkOnlyCoverage`\n    50ŌåÆ  - [x] `evaluator.test.ts` ŌĆö tests for `evaluateCoverage`, `updateCoverageState`, `checkPerFileCoverage`, `formatCoverageOutput`\n    51ŌåÆ  - [x] Delete old `src/lib/__tests__/coverage.test.ts`\n    52ŌåÆ  - [x] Update test imports in `src/modules/audit/__tests__/dimensions.test.ts` and `src/commands/__tests__/coverage.test.ts`\n    53ŌåÆ- [x] Task 9: Verify cross-domain import discipline (AC: #10)\n    54ŌåÆ  - [x] Grep for any imports from internal files of other domain dirs\n    55ŌåÆ- [x] Task 10: Run `npx tsc --noEmit` and `npm test` ŌĆö zero regressions (AC: #7, #8)\n    56ŌåÆ\n    57ŌåÆ## Dev Notes\n    58ŌåÆ\n    59ŌåÆ### Current State of coverage.ts\n    60ŌåÆ\n    61ŌåÆ- **Location:** `src/lib/coverage.ts` ŌĆö 633 lines\n    62ŌåÆ- **Exports:** 11 functions + 5 types (see AC6 for full list)\n    63ŌåÆ- **Test file:** `src/lib/__tests__/coverage.test.ts` ŌĆö 968 lines\n    64ŌåÆ\n    65ŌåÆ### Consumers (files that import from coverage.ts)\n    66ŌåÆ\n    67ŌåÆ| File | Imports |\n    68ŌåÆ|------|---------|\n    69ŌåÆ| `src/commands/coverage.ts` | `detectCoverageTool`, `runCoverage`, `checkOnlyCoverage`, `evaluateCoverage`, `updateCoverageState`, `printCoverageOutput`, `checkPerFileCoverage` |\n    70ŌåÆ| `src/modules/audit/dimensions.ts` | `checkOnlyCoverage` |\n    71ŌåÆ| `src/lib/scanner.ts` | `detectCoverageTool`, `parseCoverageReport` |\n    72ŌåÆ| `src/lib/onboard-checks.ts` | `checkPerFileCoverage` |\n    73ŌåÆ| `src/modules/audit/__tests__/dimensions.test.ts` | `checkOnlyCoverage` |\n    74ŌåÆ| `src/commands/__tests__/coverage.test.ts` | Multiple coverage imports |\n    75ŌåÆ| `src/lib/__tests__/coverage.test.ts` | All coverage imports |\n    76ŌåÆ\n    77ŌåÆ### Target File Layout (from architecture-v3.md)\n    78ŌåÆ\n    79ŌåÆ```\n    80ŌåÆsrc/lib/coverage/\n    81ŌåÆ  index.ts      # Re-exports only (<50 lines)\n    82ŌåÆ  types.ts      # CoverageToolInfo, CoverageResult, CoverageEvaluation, FileCoverageEntry, PerFileCoverageResult\n    83ŌåÆ  runner.ts     # detectCoverageTool, getTestCommand, runCoverage, checkOnlyCoverage + private helpers\n    84ŌåÆ  evaluator.ts  # evaluateCoverage, updateCoverageState, checkPerFileCoverage, formatCoverageOutput, printCoverageOutput\n    85ŌåÆ  parser.ts     # parseTestCounts, parseCoverageReport\n    86ŌåÆ```\n    87ŌåÆ\n    88ŌåÆ### Function-to-File Mapping\n    89ŌåÆ\n    90ŌåÆ| Function | Target File | Lines (approx) |\n    91ŌåÆ|----------|------------|-----------------|\n    92ŌåÆ| Types (CoverageToolInfo, CoverageResult, CoverageEvaluation, FileCoverageEntry, PerFileCoverageResult) | `types.ts` | ~40 |\n    93ŌåÆ| `detectCoverageTool`, `getTestCommand`, private detector map + helpers | `runner.ts` | ~230 |\n    94ŌåÆ| `runCoverage`, `checkOnlyCoverage` | `runner.ts` | (included above) |\n    95ŌåÆ| `parseCoverageReport`, `parseTestCounts` | `parser.ts` | ~120 |\n    96ŌåÆ| `evaluateCoverage`, `updateCoverageState`, `checkPerFileCoverage`, `formatCoverageOutput`, `printCoverageOutput` | `evaluator.ts` | ~180 |\n    97ŌåÆ| Re-exports | `index.ts` | ~30 |\n    98ŌåÆ\n    99ŌåÆ### Import Rules (architecture-v3.md, Decision 4)\n   100ŌåÆ\n   101ŌåÆ- External consumers import from `src/lib/coverage/index.ts` only\n   102ŌåÆ- Within coverage/, files can import from siblings\n   103ŌåÆ- No cross-domain internal imports ŌĆö use `../docker/index.js`, not `../docker/compose.js`\n   104ŌåÆ- `src/lib/state.ts` and `src/lib/output.ts` are shared utilities ŌĆö any file can import them\n   105ŌåÆ\n   106ŌåÆ### Dependency Graph Within coverage.ts\n   107ŌåÆ\n   108ŌåÆ- `types.ts` ŌĆö no internal dependencies (pure types)\n   109ŌåÆ- `parser.ts` ŌĆö depends on `types.ts` only\n   110ŌåÆ- `runner.ts` ŌĆö depends on `types.ts`, `parser.ts`, `../state.js`, `../output.js`, `../stacks/index.js`\n   111ŌåÆ- `evaluator.ts` ŌĆö depends on `types.ts`, `../state.js`, `../output.js`\n   112ŌåÆ\n   113ŌåÆ### Ordering Guard (AC3)\n   114ŌåÆ\n   115ŌåÆ`parseTestCounts()` currently handles cargo workspace output specially. The cargo aggregation regex must fire before the pytest fallback regex when both patterns could match. This ordering is critical and must be preserved in `parser.ts`. A dedicated test must assert that mixed cargo+pytest-like output triggers cargo aggregation, not the pytest path.\n   116ŌåÆ\n   117ŌåÆ### Project Structure Notes\n   118ŌåÆ\n   119ŌåÆ- This is Story 12-1 of Epic 12 (lib/ Restructuring). Subsequent stories (12-2 through 12-4) will follow the same split pattern for other oversized files.\n   120ŌåÆ- The patterns established here (barrel index, test organization, import conventions) will be reused by stories 12-2, 12-3, and 12-4.\n   121ŌåÆ- Do NOT create `src/lib/coverage/AGENTS.md` ŌĆö that's a modules/ convention, not a lib/ convention.\n   122ŌåÆ\n   123ŌåÆ### References\n   124ŌåÆ\n   125ŌåÆ- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/architecture-v3.md ŌĆö Decision 4: lib/ Restructuring, coverage/ section]\n   126ŌåÆ- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/epics-architecture-v3.md ŌĆö Epic 12, Story 12-1]\n   127ŌåÆ\n   128ŌåÆ<!-- CODEHARNESS-PATCH-START:story-verification -->\n   129ŌåÆ## Verification Requirements\n   130ŌåÆ\n   131ŌåÆ- [ ] Showboat proof document created (`docs/exec-plans/active/12-1-split-coverage-ts-domain-subdirectory.proof.md`)\n   132ŌåÆ- [ ] All acceptance criteria verified with real-world evidence\n   133ŌåÆ- [ ] Test coverage meets target (100%)\n   134ŌåÆ\n   135ŌåÆ## Documentation Requirements\n   136ŌåÆ\n   137ŌåÆ- [ ] Relevant AGENTS.md files updated (list modules touched)\n   138ŌåÆ- [ ] Exec-plan created in `docs/exec-plans/active/12-1-split-coverage-ts-domain-subdirectory.md`\n   139ŌåÆ\n   140ŌåÆ## Testing Requirements\n   141ŌåÆ\n   142ŌåÆ- [ ] Unit tests written for all new/changed code\n   143ŌåÆ- [ ] Integration tests for cross-module interactions\n   144ŌåÆ- [ ] Coverage target: 100%\n   145ŌåÆ<!-- CODEHARNESS-PATCH-END:story-verification -->\n   146ŌåÆ\n   147ŌåÆ## Dev Agent Record\n   148ŌåÆ\n   149ŌåÆ### Agent Model Used\n   150ŌåÆ\n   151ŌåÆClaude Opus 4.6 (1M context)\n   152ŌåÆ\n   153ŌåÆ### Debug Log References\n   154ŌåÆ\n   155ŌåÆN/A\n   156ŌåÆ\n   157ŌåÆ### Completion Notes List\n   158ŌåÆ\n   159ŌåÆ- Split `src/lib/coverage.ts` (633 lines) into 5 files under `src/lib/coverage/`: types.ts (43 lines), parser.ts (139 lines), runner.ts (284 lines), evaluator.ts (162 lines), index.ts (32 lines)\n   160ŌåÆ- All files under 300 lines, index.ts under 50 lines (pure re-exports)\n   161ŌåÆ- Reorganized tests from `src/lib/__tests__/coverage.test.ts` (968 lines) into 3 test files: parser.test.ts, runner.test.ts, evaluator.test.ts (69 tests total in coverage module)\n   162ŌåÆ- Added AC3 ordering guard test: verifies cargo aggregation fires before pytest fallback when both patterns could match\n   163ŌåÆ- Updated all 6 consumer import paths (4 source files + 2 test files) from `coverage.js` to `coverage/index.js`\n   164ŌåÆ- Deleted old `src/lib/coverage.ts` and `src/lib/__tests__/coverage.test.ts`\n   165ŌåÆ- Zero cross-domain internal imports in coverage/ ŌĆö only imports from `../state.js`, `../output.js`, `../stacks/index.js` (shared utilities and barrel exports)\n   166ŌåÆ- Full test suite: 127 files, 3448 tests, all passing, zero regressions\n   167ŌåÆ- TypeScript: zero new type errors from coverage/ files\n   168ŌåÆ- `findCoverageSummary` exported from parser.ts (needed by evaluator.ts for `checkPerFileCoverage`)\n   169ŌåÆ\n   170ŌåÆ### File List\n   171ŌåÆ\n   172ŌåÆ- `src/lib/coverage/types.ts` (new) ŌĆö All type/interface exports\n   173ŌåÆ- `src/lib/coverage/parser.ts` (new) ŌĆö parseTestCounts, parseCoverageReport, findCoverageSummary\n   174ŌåÆ- `src/lib/coverage/runner.ts` (new) ŌĆö detectCoverageTool, getTestCommand, runCoverage, checkOnlyCoverage\n   175ŌåÆ- `src/lib/coverage/evaluator.ts` (new) ŌĆö evaluateCoverage, updateCoverageState, checkPerFileCoverage, formatCoverageOutput, printCoverageOutput\n   176ŌåÆ- `src/lib/coverage/index.ts` (new) ŌĆö Barrel re-exports\n   177ŌåÆ- `src/lib/coverage/__tests__/parser.test.ts` (new) ŌĆö Parser tests including AC3 ordering guard\n   178ŌåÆ- `src/lib/coverage/__tests__/runner.test.ts` (new) ŌĆö Runner/detection tests\n   179ŌåÆ- `src/lib/coverage/__tests__/evaluator.test.ts` (new) ŌĆö Evaluator/output tests\n   180ŌåÆ- `src/lib/coverage.ts` (deleted)\n   181ŌåÆ- `src/lib/__tests__/coverage.test.ts` (deleted)\n   182ŌåÆ- `src/commands/coverage.ts` (modified) ŌĆö Import path updated\n   183ŌåÆ- `src/modules/audit/dimensions.ts` (modified) ŌĆö Import path updated\n   184ŌåÆ- `src/lib/scanner.ts` (modified) ŌĆö Import path updated\n   185ŌåÆ- `src/lib/onboard-checks.ts` (modified) ŌĆö Import path updated\n   186ŌåÆ- `src/commands/__tests__/coverage.test.ts` (modified) ŌĆö Mock and import paths updated\n   187ŌåÆ- `src/modules/audit/__tests__/dimensions.test.ts` (modified) ŌĆö Mock and import paths updated\n   188ŌåÆ"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_013A1PTE3Sqig6Yi2KxMXRHR","session_id":"010b7052-acb2-4a98-9861-0b5f61bbdbf0","uuid":"5716a1ad-7afb-4808-b0a6-daca2f895f84","timestamp":"2026-03-24T12:14:17.503Z"}
