{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01KRchM2huUQBCQHXUMJ3Lka","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01CySPKN7VBkAeipCwttpgdL","name":"Read","input":{"file_path":"/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad/bmm/workflows/4-implementation/code-review/instructions.xml"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":187,"cache_read_input_tokens":15189,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":187,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":54,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_013A1PTE3Sqig6Yi2KxMXRHR","session_id":"010b7052-acb2-4a98-9861-0b5f61bbdbf0","uuid":"6ec13697-a18a-435d-8838-8ba8ee6e5c99"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01CySPKN7VBkAeipCwttpgdL","type":"tool_result","content":"     1ŌåÆ<workflow>\n     2ŌåÆ  <critical>The workflow execution engine is governed by: {project-root}/_bmad/core/tasks/workflow.xml</critical>\n     3ŌåÆ  <critical>You MUST have already loaded and processed: {installed_path}/workflow.yaml</critical>\n     4ŌåÆ  <critical>Communicate all responses in {communication_language} and language MUST be tailored to {user_skill_level}</critical>\n     5ŌåÆ  <critical>Generate all documents in {document_output_language}</critical>\n     6ŌåÆ\n     7ŌåÆ  <critical>­¤öź YOU ARE AN ADVERSARIAL CODE REVIEWER - Find what's wrong or missing! ­¤öź</critical>\n     8ŌåÆ  <critical>Your purpose: Validate story file claims against actual implementation</critical>\n     9ŌåÆ  <critical>Challenge everything: Are tasks marked [x] actually done? Are ACs really implemented?</critical>\n    10ŌåÆ  <critical>Find 3-10 specific issues in every review minimum - no lazy \"looks good\" reviews - YOU are so much better than the dev agent\n    11ŌåÆ    that wrote this slop</critical>\n    12ŌåÆ  <critical>Read EVERY file in the File List - verify implementation against story requirements</critical>\n    13ŌåÆ  <critical>Tasks marked complete but not done = CRITICAL finding</critical>\n    14ŌåÆ  <critical>Acceptance Criteria not implemented = HIGH severity finding</critical>\n    15ŌåÆ  <critical>Do not review files that are not part of the application's source code. Always exclude the _bmad/ and _bmad-output/ folders from the review. Always exclude IDE and CLI configuration folders like .cursor/ and .windsurf/ and .claude/</critical>\n    16ŌåÆ\n    17ŌåÆ\n    18ŌåÆ  <step n=\"1\" goal=\"Load story and discover changes\">\n    19ŌåÆ    <action>Use provided {{story_path}} or ask user which story file to review</action>\n    20ŌåÆ    <action>Read COMPLETE story file</action>\n    21ŌåÆ    <action>Set {{story_key}} = extracted key from filename (e.g., \"1-2-user-authentication.md\" ŌåÆ \"1-2-user-authentication\") or story\n    22ŌåÆ      metadata</action>\n    23ŌåÆ    <action>Parse sections: Story, Acceptance Criteria, Tasks/Subtasks, Dev Agent Record ŌåÆ File List, Change Log</action>\n    24ŌåÆ\n    25ŌåÆ    <!-- Discover actual changes via git -->\n    26ŌåÆ    <action>Check if git repository detected in current directory</action>\n    27ŌåÆ    <check if=\"git repository exists\">\n    28ŌåÆ      <action>Run `git status --porcelain` to find uncommitted changes</action>\n    29ŌåÆ      <action>Run `git diff --name-only` to see modified files</action>\n    30ŌåÆ      <action>Run `git diff --cached --name-only` to see staged files</action>\n    31ŌåÆ      <action>Compile list of actually changed files from git output</action>\n    32ŌåÆ    </check>\n    33ŌåÆ\n    34ŌåÆ    <!-- Cross-reference story File List vs git reality -->\n    35ŌåÆ    <action>Compare story's Dev Agent Record ŌåÆ File List with actual git changes</action>\n    36ŌåÆ    <action>Note discrepancies:\n    37ŌåÆ      - Files in git but not in story File List\n    38ŌåÆ      - Files in story File List but no git changes\n    39ŌåÆ      - Missing documentation of what was actually changed\n    40ŌåÆ    </action>\n    41ŌåÆ\n    42ŌåÆ    <invoke-protocol name=\"discover_inputs\" />\n    43ŌåÆ    <action>Load {project_context} for coding standards (if exists)</action>\n    44ŌåÆ  </step>\n    45ŌåÆ\n    46ŌåÆ  <step n=\"2\" goal=\"Build review attack plan\">\n    47ŌåÆ    <action>Extract ALL Acceptance Criteria from story</action>\n    48ŌåÆ    <action>Extract ALL Tasks/Subtasks with completion status ([x] vs [ ])</action>\n    49ŌåÆ    <action>From Dev Agent Record ŌåÆ File List, compile list of claimed changes</action>\n    50ŌåÆ\n    51ŌåÆ    <action>Create review plan:\n    52ŌåÆ      1. **AC Validation**: Verify each AC is actually implemented\n    53ŌåÆ      2. **Task Audit**: Verify each [x] task is really done\n    54ŌåÆ      3. **Code Quality**: Security, performance, maintainability\n    55ŌåÆ      4. **Test Quality**: Real tests vs placeholder bullshit\n    56ŌåÆ    </action>\n    57ŌåÆ  </step>\n    58ŌåÆ\n    59ŌåÆ  <step n=\"3\" goal=\"Execute adversarial review\">\n    60ŌåÆ    <critical>VALIDATE EVERY CLAIM - Check git reality vs story claims</critical>\n    61ŌåÆ\n    62ŌåÆ    <!-- Git vs Story Discrepancies -->\n    63ŌåÆ    <action>Review git vs story File List discrepancies:\n    64ŌåÆ      1. **Files changed but not in story File List** ŌåÆ MEDIUM finding (incomplete documentation)\n    65ŌåÆ      2. **Story lists files but no git changes** ŌåÆ HIGH finding (false claims)\n    66ŌåÆ      3. **Uncommitted changes not documented** ŌåÆ MEDIUM finding (transparency issue)\n    67ŌåÆ    </action>\n    68ŌåÆ\n    69ŌåÆ    <!-- Use combined file list: story File List + git discovered files -->\n    70ŌåÆ    <action>Create comprehensive review file list from story File List and git changes</action>\n    71ŌåÆ\n    72ŌåÆ    <!-- AC Validation -->\n    73ŌåÆ    <action>For EACH Acceptance Criterion:\n    74ŌåÆ      1. Read the AC requirement\n    75ŌåÆ      2. Search implementation files for evidence\n    76ŌåÆ      3. Determine: IMPLEMENTED, PARTIAL, or MISSING\n    77ŌåÆ      4. If MISSING/PARTIAL ŌåÆ HIGH SEVERITY finding\n    78ŌåÆ    </action>\n    79ŌåÆ\n    80ŌåÆ    <!-- Task Completion Audit -->\n    81ŌåÆ    <action>For EACH task marked [x]:\n    82ŌåÆ      1. Read the task description\n    83ŌåÆ      2. Search files for evidence it was actually done\n    84ŌåÆ      3. **CRITICAL**: If marked [x] but NOT DONE ŌåÆ CRITICAL finding\n    85ŌåÆ      4. Record specific proof (file:line)\n    86ŌåÆ    </action>\n    87ŌåÆ\n    88ŌåÆ    <!-- Code Quality Deep Dive -->\n    89ŌåÆ    <action>For EACH file in comprehensive review list:\n    90ŌåÆ      1. **Security**: Look for injection risks, missing validation, auth issues\n    91ŌåÆ      2. **Performance**: N+1 queries, inefficient loops, missing caching\n    92ŌåÆ      3. **Error Handling**: Missing try/catch, poor error messages\n    93ŌåÆ      4. **Code Quality**: Complex functions, magic numbers, poor naming\n    94ŌåÆ      5. **Test Quality**: Are tests real assertions or placeholders?\n    95ŌåÆ    </action>\n    96ŌåÆ\n    97ŌåÆ    <check if=\"total_issues_found lt 3\">\n    98ŌåÆ      <critical>NOT LOOKING HARD ENOUGH - Find more problems!</critical>\n    99ŌåÆ      <action>Re-examine code for:\n   100ŌåÆ        - Edge cases and null handling\n   101ŌåÆ        - Architecture violations\n   102ŌåÆ        - Documentation gaps\n   103ŌåÆ        - Integration issues\n   104ŌåÆ        - Dependency problems\n   105ŌåÆ        - Git commit message quality (if applicable)\n   106ŌåÆ      </action>\n   107ŌåÆ      <action>Find at least 3 more specific, actionable issues</action>\n   108ŌåÆ    </check>\n   109ŌåÆ  </step>\n   110ŌåÆ\n   111ŌåÆ  <step n=\"4\" goal=\"Present findings and fix them\">\n   112ŌåÆ    <action>Categorize findings: HIGH (must fix), MEDIUM (should fix), LOW (nice to fix)</action>\n   113ŌåÆ    <action>Set {{fixed_count}} = 0</action>\n   114ŌåÆ    <action>Set {{action_count}} = 0</action>\n   115ŌåÆ\n   116ŌåÆ    <output>**­¤öź CODE REVIEW FINDINGS, {user_name}!**\n   117ŌåÆ\n   118ŌåÆ      **Story:** {{story_file}}\n   119ŌåÆ      **Git vs Story Discrepancies:** {{git_discrepancy_count}} found\n   120ŌåÆ      **Issues Found:** {{high_count}} High, {{medium_count}} Medium, {{low_count}} Low\n   121ŌåÆ\n   122ŌåÆ      ## ­¤ö┤ CRITICAL ISSUES\n   123ŌåÆ      - Tasks marked [x] but not actually implemented\n   124ŌåÆ      - Acceptance Criteria not implemented\n   125ŌåÆ      - Story claims files changed but no git evidence\n   126ŌåÆ      - Security vulnerabilities\n   127ŌåÆ\n   128ŌåÆ      ## ­¤¤Ī MEDIUM ISSUES\n   129ŌåÆ      - Files changed but not documented in story File List\n   130ŌåÆ      - Uncommitted changes not tracked\n   131ŌåÆ      - Performance problems\n   132ŌåÆ      - Poor test coverage/quality\n   133ŌåÆ      - Code maintainability issues\n   134ŌåÆ\n   135ŌåÆ      ## ­¤¤ó LOW ISSUES\n   136ŌåÆ      - Code style improvements\n   137ŌåÆ      - Documentation gaps\n   138ŌåÆ      - Git commit message quality\n   139ŌåÆ    </output>\n   140ŌåÆ\n   141ŌåÆ    <ask>What should I do with these issues?\n   142ŌåÆ\n   143ŌåÆ      1. **Fix them automatically** - I'll update the code and tests\n   144ŌåÆ      2. **Create action items** - Add to story Tasks/Subtasks for later\n   145ŌåÆ      3. **Show me details** - Deep dive into specific issues\n   146ŌåÆ\n   147ŌåÆ      Choose [1], [2], or specify which issue to examine:</ask>\n   148ŌåÆ\n   149ŌåÆ    <check if=\"user chooses 1\">\n   150ŌåÆ      <action>Fix all HIGH and MEDIUM issues in the code</action>\n   151ŌåÆ      <action>Add/update tests as needed</action>\n   152ŌåÆ      <action>Update File List in story if files changed</action>\n   153ŌåÆ      <action>Update story Dev Agent Record with fixes applied</action>\n   154ŌåÆ      <action>Set {{fixed_count}} = number of HIGH and MEDIUM issues fixed</action>\n   155ŌåÆ      <action>Set {{action_count}} = 0</action>\n   156ŌåÆ    </check>\n   157ŌåÆ\n   158ŌåÆ    <check if=\"user chooses 2\">\n   159ŌåÆ      <action>Add \"Review Follow-ups (AI)\" subsection to Tasks/Subtasks</action>\n   160ŌåÆ      <action>For each issue: `- [ ] [AI-Review][Severity] Description [file:line]`</action>\n   161ŌåÆ      <action>Set {{action_count}} = number of action items created</action>\n   162ŌåÆ      <action>Set {{fixed_count}} = 0</action>\n   163ŌåÆ    </check>\n   164ŌåÆ\n   165ŌåÆ    <check if=\"user chooses 3\">\n   166ŌåÆ      <action>Show detailed explanation with code examples</action>\n   167ŌåÆ      <action>Return to fix decision</action>\n   168ŌåÆ    </check>\n   169ŌåÆ  </step>\n   170ŌåÆ\n   171ŌåÆ  <!-- CODEHARNESS-PATCH-START:review-enforcement -->\n   172ŌåÆ  <step n=\"4.5\" goal=\"Harness verification checks\">\n   173ŌåÆ    <critical>Codeharness requires these additional review checks</critical>\n   174ŌåÆ    <action>Verify Showboat proof document exists at docs/exec-plans/active/{{story_key}}.proof.md or docs/exec-plans/completed/{{story_key}}.proof.md</action>\n   175ŌåÆ    <action>Check AGENTS.md freshness ŌĆö all modules in File List must have up-to-date AGENTS.md</action>\n   176ŌåÆ    <action>Verify test coverage meets 100% target for all changed modules</action>\n   177ŌåÆ    <action if=\"proof document missing\">Add HIGH finding: \"Missing Showboat proof document\"</action>\n   178ŌåÆ    <action if=\"AGENTS.md stale or missing for changed module\">Add MEDIUM finding: \"AGENTS.md missing or stale for {{module}}\"</action>\n   179ŌåÆ    <action if=\"coverage below target\">Add HIGH finding: \"Test coverage below 100% target\"</action>\n   180ŌåÆ  </step>\n   181ŌåÆ  <!-- CODEHARNESS-PATCH-END:review-enforcement -->\n   182ŌåÆ\n   183ŌåÆ  <step n=\"5\" goal=\"Update story status and sync sprint tracking\">\n   184ŌåÆ    <!-- Determine new status based on review outcome -->\n   185ŌåÆ    <check if=\"all HIGH and MEDIUM issues fixed AND all ACs implemented\">\n   186ŌåÆ      <action>Set {{new_status}} = \"done\"</action>\n   187ŌåÆ      <action>Update story Status field to \"done\"</action>\n   188ŌåÆ    </check>\n   189ŌåÆ    <check if=\"HIGH or MEDIUM issues remain OR ACs not fully implemented\">\n   190ŌåÆ      <action>Set {{new_status}} = \"in-progress\"</action>\n   191ŌåÆ      <action>Update story Status field to \"in-progress\"</action>\n   192ŌåÆ    </check>\n   193ŌåÆ    <action>Save story file</action>\n   194ŌåÆ\n   195ŌåÆ    <!-- Determine sprint tracking status -->\n   196ŌåÆ    <check if=\"{sprint_status} file exists\">\n   197ŌåÆ      <action>Set {{current_sprint_status}} = \"enabled\"</action>\n   198ŌåÆ    </check>\n   199ŌåÆ    <check if=\"{sprint_status} file does NOT exist\">\n   200ŌåÆ      <action>Set {{current_sprint_status}} = \"no-sprint-tracking\"</action>\n   201ŌåÆ    </check>\n   202ŌåÆ\n   203ŌåÆ    <!-- Sync sprint-status.yaml when story status changes (only if sprint tracking enabled) -->\n   204ŌåÆ    <check if=\"{{current_sprint_status}} != 'no-sprint-tracking'\">\n   205ŌåÆ      <action>Load the FULL file: {sprint_status}</action>\n   206ŌåÆ      <action>Find development_status key matching {{story_key}}</action>\n   207ŌåÆ\n   208ŌåÆ      <check if=\"{{new_status}} == 'done'\">\n   209ŌåÆ        <action>Update development_status[{{story_key}}] = \"done\"</action>\n   210ŌåÆ        <action>Save file, preserving ALL comments and structure</action>\n   211ŌåÆ        <output>Ō£ģ Sprint status synced: {{story_key}} ŌåÆ done</output>\n   212ŌåÆ      </check>\n   213ŌåÆ\n   214ŌåÆ      <check if=\"{{new_status}} == 'in-progress'\">\n   215ŌåÆ        <action>Update development_status[{{story_key}}] = \"in-progress\"</action>\n   216ŌåÆ        <action>Save file, preserving ALL comments and structure</action>\n   217ŌåÆ        <output>­¤öä Sprint status synced: {{story_key}} ŌåÆ in-progress</output>\n   218ŌåÆ      </check>\n   219ŌåÆ\n   220ŌåÆ      <check if=\"story key not found in sprint status\">\n   221ŌåÆ        <output>ŌÜĀ’ĖÅ Story file updated, but sprint-status sync failed: {{story_key}} not found in sprint-status.yaml</output>\n   222ŌåÆ      </check>\n   223ŌåÆ    </check>\n   224ŌåÆ\n   225ŌåÆ    <check if=\"{{current_sprint_status}} == 'no-sprint-tracking'\">\n   226ŌåÆ      <output>Ōä╣’ĖÅ Story status updated (no sprint tracking configured)</output>\n   227ŌåÆ    </check>\n   228ŌåÆ\n   229ŌåÆ    <output>**Ō£ģ Review Complete!**\n   230ŌåÆ\n   231ŌåÆ      **Story Status:** {{new_status}}\n   232ŌåÆ      **Issues Fixed:** {{fixed_count}}\n   233ŌåÆ      **Action Items Created:** {{action_count}}\n   234ŌåÆ\n   235ŌåÆ      {{#if new_status == \"done\"}}Code review complete!{{else}}Address the action items and continue development.{{/if}}\n   236ŌåÆ    </output>\n   237ŌåÆ  </step>\n