{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01T5bGeRjtgvhLsi4rsUcogv","type":"tool_result","content":"     1ŌåÆ# Session Issues Log ŌĆö 2026-03-24\n     2ŌåÆ\n     3ŌåÆ### 11-3-state-reconciliation-on-session-start ŌĆö create-story (2026-03-24T11:34:00Z)\n     4ŌåÆ\n     5ŌåÆ- Epic definition had only 1 AC; expanded to 12 ACs by examining codebase\n     6ŌåÆ- Risk: parseStoryKey() returns [Infinity, Infinity] for non-matching keys ŌĆö edge case needs handling\n     7ŌåÆ- Risk: orphan file deletion (ACs 3-4) is one-way; must delete AFTER successful state write\n     8ŌåÆ- writeStateAtomic() already calls writeSprintStatusYaml() ŌĆö reconcileState() may cause double YAML generation\n     9ŌåÆ- retry-state.ts has @deprecated comments saying \"will be removed in story 11-3\" for legacy path helpers\n    10ŌåÆ- run.ts still reads ralph/.flagged_stories directly (line 93-101), bypassing sprint-state.json flagged field ŌĆö must update before file deletion\n    11ŌåÆ\n    12ŌåÆ### 11-3-state-reconciliation-on-session-start ŌĆö dev-story (2026-03-24T11:45:00Z)\n    13ŌåÆ\n    14ŌåÆ- Pre-existing ~60 type errors in unrelated test files (not introduced by this story)\n    15ŌåÆ- Readonly mutation workaround: uses JSON.parse(JSON.stringify(...)) deep clone + type assertions to mutate SprintState clone\n    16ŌåÆ- YAML always regenerated even in no-op case ŌĆö cheap but could be optimized to skip if content unchanged\n    17ŌåÆ\n    18ŌåÆ### 12-1-split-coverage-ts-domain-subdirectory ŌĆö create-story (2026-03-24T12:01:00Z)\n    19ŌåÆ\n    20ŌåÆ- Workflow file was `workflow.yaml` not `workflow.md` ŌĆö skill invocation message referenced `.md` but only `.yaml` existed\n    21ŌåÆ- Subagent was instructed not to modify sprint-status.yaml; main agent had to update manually\n    22ŌåÆ- Risk: runner.ts may push past 300 lines if all private helpers are large (~230 line estimate is rough)\n    23ŌåÆ- Risk: AC11 (integration-required) tests e2e CLI behavior identity, requires real project with test runner configured\n    24ŌåÆ- `coverage.ts` is 633 lines (not 617 as stated in architecture-v3.md ŌĆö grew since doc was written)\n    25ŌåÆ- This establishes the first domain subdirectory pattern in src/lib/ ŌĆö stories 12-2 through 12-4 will follow it\n    26ŌåÆ\n    27ŌåÆ### 12-1-split-coverage-ts-domain-subdirectory ŌĆö dev-story (2026-03-24T12:04:00Z)\n    28ŌåÆ\n    29ŌåÆNo issues reported (subagent reported \"None\").\n    30ŌåÆ\n    31ŌåÆ### 12-1-split-coverage-ts-domain-subdirectory ŌĆö code-review (2026-03-24T12:14:00Z)\n    32ŌåÆ\n    33ŌåÆ- HIGH: runner.ts statement coverage at 78.15% (below 80% per-file floor). Fixed ŌĆö now 95.79% (+11 new tests)\n    34ŌåÆ- MEDIUM (unfixed tech debt): `findCoverageSummary` exported from parser.ts but not from index.ts barrel. Used only by evaluator.ts as sibling import.\n    35ŌåÆ- LOW: `error: required option '--story <key>' not specified` noise during `codeharness coverage` runs from other commands registering at startup\n    36ŌåÆ- No integration test exercises full `runCoverage` pipeline end-to-end (AC11 integration-required)\n    37ŌåÆ- index.ts and types.ts show 0% coverage (pure type exports, expected)\n    38ŌåÆ"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_011z4gzYDMzzA1ebYMdwhV27","session_id":"010b7052-acb2-4a98-9861-0b5f61bbdbf0","uuid":"5d07825c-c355-4021-bc2f-34132983bde7","timestamp":"2026-03-24T12:26:52.571Z"}
