{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01VpgvtvH57HQK7W9m5njd6u","type":"tool_result","content":"     1ŌåÆ# Session Retrospective ŌĆö 2026-03-24\n     2ŌåÆ\n     3ŌåÆ**Sprint:** Operational Excellence (Architecture v3 Migration phase)\n     4ŌåÆ**Session:** 8 (continuation from session 7 on 2026-03-23)\n     5ŌåÆ**Session start:** ~07:39 UTC\n     6ŌåÆ\n     7ŌåÆ---\n     8ŌåÆ\n     9ŌåÆ## 1. Session Summary\n    10ŌåÆ\n    11ŌåÆ| Story | Epic | Outcome | Pipeline Stages |\n    12ŌåÆ|-------|------|---------|-----------------|\n    13ŌåÆ| 9-2-state-schema-migration-multi-stack | Epic 9 (Multi-Stack) | done (carryover from session 7) | create-story, dev-story, code-review all completed |\n    14ŌåÆ| 10-1-stackprovider-interface-and-registry | Epic 10 (Stack Provider Pattern) | done ŌĆö status: verifying | create-story, dev-story, code-review all completed |\n    15ŌåÆ\n    16ŌåÆBoth stories completed all pipeline stages (story creation, development, code review with fixes). Story 9-2 was carried over from session 7 (2026-03-23) where it went through create-story and dev-story; code review happened at the boundary. Story 10-1 was fully executed in this session.\n    17ŌåÆ\n    18ŌåÆ**Net progress:** Epic 9 fully closed (all 5 stories done). Epic 10 started ŌĆö 1 of 5 stories done, 4 remain in backlog.\n    19ŌåÆ\n    20ŌåÆ---\n    21ŌåÆ\n    22ŌåÆ## 2. Issues Analysis\n    23ŌåÆ\n    24ŌåÆ### Bugs Discovered During Implementation or Verification\n    25ŌåÆ\n    26ŌåÆ| Severity | Story | Issue | Fixed? |\n    27ŌåÆ|----------|-------|-------|--------|\n    28ŌåÆ| HIGH | 9-2 | `init-project.ts` never persisted multi-stacks to state file ŌĆö `detectStacks()` results lost on init | Yes |\n    29ŌåÆ| HIGH | 10-1 | `src/lib/stacks/index.ts` barrel file at 0% coverage ŌĆö auto-registration never tested | Yes |\n    30ŌåÆ| HIGH | 10-1 | `src/lib/stacks/nodejs.ts` at 17.64% coverage ŌĆö 13 stub methods uncalled | Yes |\n    31ŌåÆ| MEDIUM | 9-2 | `writeState()` mutated caller's state object via `state.stack = state.stacks[0]` side effect | Yes |\n    32ŌåÆ| MEDIUM | 9-2 | `isValidState()` accepted `stacks: [42, true]` ŌĆö no element type checking | Yes |\n    33ŌåÆ| MEDIUM | 9-2 | `recoverCorruptedState()` produced inconsistent `stack: null` / `stacks: ['nodejs']` | Yes |\n    34ŌåÆ| MEDIUM | 10-1 | Bare `catch {}` in registry.ts line 73 ŌĆö readdirSync errors silently swallowed | Yes |\n    35ŌåÆ\n    36ŌåÆCode review caught 7 HIGH/MEDIUM bugs across both stories. All were fixed in-session. The `init-project.ts` persistence bug (9-2) was the most impactful ŌĆö multi-stack detection would have been silently broken at runtime.\n    37ŌåÆ\n    38ŌåÆ### Workarounds Applied (Tech Debt Introduced)\n    39ŌåÆ\n    40ŌåÆ1. **`stacks: ['nodejs'] as StackName[]`** in `stack.test.ts` ŌĆö readonly tuple workaround. Minor, localized to tests.\n    41ŌåÆ2. **`migrateState()` casts `raw.stack as StackName`** without validating against known stack names (9-2, LOW, not fixed). Invalid stack names in old state files would pass migration unchecked.\n    42ŌåÆ3. **`recoverCorruptedState()` calls both `detectStack()` and `detectStacks()`** ŌĆö double detection (9-2, LOW, not fixed). Performance waste, not a correctness issue.\n    43ŌåÆ\n    44ŌåÆ### Code Quality Concerns\n    45ŌåÆ\n    46ŌåÆ1. **`StackDetection` type duplicated** between `registry.ts` and `stack-detect.ts` (10-1, MEDIUM, deferred to story 10-5). Expected ŌĆö the old and new codepaths coexist until consumer migration.\n    47ŌåÆ2. **`_resetRegistry` test-only utility leaking into public barrel export** (10-1, LOW, not fixed). Should be conditionally exported or moved to test helpers.\n    48ŌåÆ3. **Parallel detection codepaths** ŌĆö `stack-detect.ts` retains hardcoded detection while `registry.ts` has marker-based detection. Two ways to detect stacks coexist until story 10-5.\n    49ŌåÆ4. **~10 pre-existing TS compilation errors** in test files (bridge, run